WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:05:36.378 --> 00:05:37.425
Move!

3
00:08:21.918 --> 00:08:23.438
It's life or death now. James.

4
00:08:25.130 --> 00:08:27.883
By that.
I mean you're doing one or the other

5
00:08:29.467 --> 00:08:31.140
up in Rockview.

6
00:08:32.804 --> 00:08:34.602
This here is
District Attorney Rodin.

7
00:08:36.433 --> 00:08:38.060
Want to know what he's wondering?

8
00:08:38.768 --> 00:08:41.487
Whether you're gonna walk
like a man or cry like a pussy

9
00:08:41.604 --> 00:08:43.322
on your way to the death house.

10
00:08:43.982 --> 00:08:45.825
See. the D.A. likes the needle.

11
00:08:46.151 --> 00:08:47.903
whereas me.

12
00:08:47.986 --> 00:08:50.830
I like to see a man like you
live a long life

13
00:08:51.156 --> 00:08:52.829
with all your teeth knocked out.

14
00:08:53.158 --> 00:08:57.004
Passed around till a brother
can't tell your fart from a yawn.

15
00:08:57.662 --> 00:08:59.342
Now. I don't know
what kind of man you are.

16
00:08:59.414 --> 00:09:01.166
which of these two fates you prefer.

17
00:09:01.291 --> 00:09:05.842
but Rodin here is a generous fellow.
He's willing to let you take your pick.

18
00:09:06.504 --> 00:09:11.180
If you save us and this city
a long and costly trial.

19
00:09:11.468 --> 00:09:15.644
waive your right to counsel and confess.
right now.

20
00:09:27.025 --> 00:09:28.322
Sixteen hours.

21
00:09:28.443 --> 00:09:30.866
Has to be some kind of
record. Detective.

22
00:09:35.867 --> 00:09:37.540
What the hell is this?

23
00:09:48.505 --> 00:09:50.553
Who the hell is Jack Reacher?

24
00:09:52.383 --> 00:09:53.885
<i>Jack Reacher.</i>

25
00:09:54.052 --> 00:09:58.398
born Jack. not John. no middle name.
is a ghost.

26
00:09:58.723 --> 00:10:03.024
No driver's license. current or expired.
No residence. current or former.

27
00:10:03.228 --> 00:10:08.234
No credit cards. no credit history.
No P.O. box. cell phone. e-mail.

28
00:10:08.691 --> 00:10:09.908
Nothing.

29
00:10:10.026 --> 00:10:11.528
Can you at least tell me who he is?

30
00:10:11.736 --> 00:10:14.740
Well. I can tell you who he was.
Blood military.

31
00:10:14.864 --> 00:10:17.037
<i>Born and raised on bases abroad.</i>

32
00:10:17.575 --> 00:10:20.078
<i>Mother was a French national.
father in the Corps.</i>

33
00:10:20.370 --> 00:10:23.715
<i>His first trip to the United States
was to attend West Point.</i>

34
00:10:23.832 --> 00:10:25.709
<i>Four years later. he ships out for good.</i>

35
00:10:26.209 --> 00:10:29.679
<i>Iraq. Afghanistan. The Balkans.
You name it.</i>

36
00:10:29.921 --> 00:10:32.094
<i>Served with distinction.</i>

37
00:10:32.257 --> 00:10:35.431
<i>Silver Star. Bronze Star.
Legion of Merit.</i>

38
00:10:36.052 --> 00:10:40.398
Defence Superior Service Medal?
Had to look that one up.

39
00:10:40.598 --> 00:10:43.021
And a Purple Heart.
He spent the bulk of his service

40
00:10:43.226 --> 00:10:47.231
in the Military Police.
By all accounts. a brilliant investigator.

41
00:10:47.730 --> 00:10:49.778
Apparently. a troublemaker. too.

42
00:10:50.108 --> 00:10:51.451
<i>Demoted to Captain.</i>

43
00:10:51.776 --> 00:10:53.198
<i>Worked his way back to Major.</i>

44
00:10:53.945 --> 00:10:56.619
<i>Then two years ago. he musters out.</i>

45
00:10:56.948 --> 00:11:01.954
<i>After a literal lifetime in the military.
he just up and quits. And then.</i>

46
00:11:02.120 --> 00:11:04.122
for only the second time in his life.

47
00:11:04.247 --> 00:11:08.093
he enters the United States
and simply disappears.

48
00:11:08.751 --> 00:11:09.877
<i>Dead. maybe?</i>

49
00:11:09.961 --> 00:11:11.562
<i>Not according
to Social Security</i>

50
00:11:11.629 --> 00:11:13.552
<i>and a bank account in Virginia.</i>

51
00:11:13.756 --> 00:11:15.929
<i>His pension is deposited monthly</i>

52
00:11:16.050 --> 00:11:20.226
<i>and someone is making the occasional
withdrawal. All wire transfers.</i>

53
00:11:21.222 --> 00:11:23.896
<i>I can't find out where
without a federal warrant.</i>

54
00:11:24.726 --> 00:11:26.444
<i>Well. he can't drive or fly.</i>

55
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:27.987
<i>At least not under his real name.</i>

56
00:11:29.606 --> 00:11:31.734
<i>- Any warrants?</i>
<i>- Records clean.</i>

57
00:11:31.941 --> 00:11:35.286
Oh. come on! A guy this hard to find?
Gotta be wanted for something.

58
00:11:35.570 --> 00:11:36.913
His record is clean.

59
00:11:37.780 --> 00:11:38.952
So.

60
00:11:42.911 --> 00:11:44.584
How do we find this Reacher?

61
00:11:44.913 --> 00:11:48.167
Obviously. you don't find this guy
unless he wants to be found.

62
00:11:50.084 --> 00:11:53.588
Excuse me. sir. There's
a Jack Reacher here to see you.

63
00:12:01.930 --> 00:12:03.147
Can I help you?

64
00:12:03.765 --> 00:12:05.642
James Barr.

65
00:12:12.982 --> 00:12:15.781
So. now you've seen him.
How do you know him?

66
00:12:16.486 --> 00:12:18.329
Why wasn't he in protective custody?

67
00:12:19.948 --> 00:12:21.575
That was an oversight.

68
00:12:21.658 --> 00:12:24.002
More like some Corrections flunky
threw him to the wolves.

69
00:12:24.702 --> 00:12:25.954
Just as likely.

70
00:12:26.120 --> 00:12:28.122
But it's done and we can't undo it.

71
00:12:28.331 --> 00:12:29.378
So what happens now?

72
00:12:29.624 --> 00:12:31.797
Well. now he's in a coma.

73
00:12:32.627 --> 00:12:35.631
We'll try him when he wakes up.
If he wakes up.

74
00:12:35.964 --> 00:12:37.386
Okay? Now it's your turn. Reacher.

75
00:12:37.799 --> 00:12:39.801
Why did he call you as a witness?

76
00:12:40.134 --> 00:12:41.477
I don't believe he did.

77
00:12:41.678 --> 00:12:43.279
Well. I believe
he asked for you by name.

78
00:12:44.347 --> 00:12:45.908
Any chance I could look
at the evidence?

79
00:12:46.140 --> 00:12:47.608
No way.
Not till you answer some questions.

80
00:12:47.684 --> 00:12:48.936
Nice meeting you.

81
00:12:49.018 --> 00:12:50.361
- Hey. Hey. Hey!
- Mr Reacher.

82
00:12:50.520 --> 00:12:51.988
- Mr Reacher!
- Hey. stop! Stop right there!

83
00:12:52.063 --> 00:12:53.440
We had a deal.

84
00:12:53.523 --> 00:12:55.776
I take you to Barr.
you tell me what you know.

85
00:12:55.858 --> 00:12:58.611
I know you say he shot five people.
I know he's in a coma.

86
00:12:58.695 --> 00:12:59.821
I know there's a bus station
three miles away

87
00:12:59.988 --> 00:13:01.740
and I can walk there in 24 minutes.

88
00:13:01.864 --> 00:13:03.207
So you're just going to
walk out on your friend?

89
00:13:03.700 --> 00:13:05.953
- He's not my friend.
- Why'd he ask for you. then?

90
00:13:06.035 --> 00:13:09.039
Well. same reason he shot five people.
he's crazy.

91
00:13:09.163 --> 00:13:10.210
Hey. Hold on.

92
00:13:10.498 --> 00:13:11.545
Don't do that.

93
00:13:11.708 --> 00:13:13.335
Well. this is a new low.
even for both of you.

94
00:13:13.418 --> 00:13:14.510
Uh-oh.

95
00:13:14.711 --> 00:13:16.304
You do not talk to my client
without me present.

96
00:13:16.379 --> 00:13:17.426
You know that.

97
00:13:17.547 --> 00:13:20.676
We weren't talking to your client.
He's in a coma. for Christ's sakes.

98
00:13:20.758 --> 00:13:23.261
- You're Barr's attorney?
- Helen Rodin. Jack Reacher.

99
00:13:23.428 --> 00:13:25.180
- Jack Reacher?
- Helen Rodin.

100
00:13:25.346 --> 00:13:26.893
Yeah. she's the
District Attorney's daughter.

101
00:13:27.015 --> 00:13:28.016
It's a good story. actually.

102
00:13:28.099 --> 00:13:29.225
I'd like to hear it.

103
00:13:29.434 --> 00:13:31.436
How'd you find him?
How'd they find you?

104
00:13:31.561 --> 00:13:34.064
You can't be talking to this man.
Two strikes in one day.

105
00:13:34.188 --> 00:13:36.029
- It's not what it looks like.
- He came to us.

106
00:13:36.524 --> 00:13:38.777
- You went to the D.A.?
- Is there a law against that?

107
00:13:38.943 --> 00:13:40.286
None you're currently breaking.

108
00:13:40.528 --> 00:13:42.451
Come on. before this gets awkward.
Now. hey.

109
00:13:42.572 --> 00:13:44.870
Say. "See you in court." For me.

110
00:13:45.116 --> 00:13:46.538
Good bye. Detective.

111
00:13:46.868 --> 00:13:48.541
- Weird meeting you.
- Likewise.

112
00:13:48.870 --> 00:13:49.962
Let's go.

113
00:13:52.749 --> 00:13:54.046
So...

114
00:13:57.211 --> 00:13:58.554
So. you're Jack Reacher.

115
00:13:58.880 --> 00:14:01.383
- So you're the D.A.'s daughter.
- Oh. Jesus. Please.

116
00:14:01.466 --> 00:14:03.309
- Is that even legal?
- Fortunately.

117
00:14:03.551 --> 00:14:05.792
- How does that happen?
- I'll tell you after deposition.

118
00:14:05.803 --> 00:14:06.924
You don't want to depose me.

119
00:14:06.971 --> 00:14:08.097
Oh. well. you're my only
defence witness.

120
00:14:08.222 --> 00:14:10.896
- I'm not a defence witness.
- Your friend James thinks you are.

121
00:14:10.975 --> 00:14:12.477
He's not my friend.
Why does everyone assume that?

122
00:14:12.602 --> 00:14:13.603
Well. why else would he ask for you

123
00:14:13.728 --> 00:14:14.729
and why would you
come here to help him?

124
00:14:14.812 --> 00:14:18.237
I didn't come here to help him.
I came here to bury him.

125
00:14:43.633 --> 00:14:44.850
Linsky.

126
00:14:47.178 --> 00:14:48.805
Who the hell is Jack Reacher?

127
00:14:50.640 --> 00:14:53.281
- So why are you so hard to find?
- I'm impossible to find.

128
00:14:53.351 --> 00:14:54.477
Why is that?

129
00:14:54.811 --> 00:14:57.985
Well. you could say it started out as an
exercise and became an addiction.

130
00:14:58.648 --> 00:15:00.150
Are you on the run?

131
00:15:02.527 --> 00:15:04.700
My bus is leaving.
You better hurry. counsellor.

132
00:15:04.821 --> 00:15:05.902
How do you know James Barr?

133
00:15:05.988 --> 00:15:07.615
- Why are you representing him?
- I'm a lawyer.

134
00:15:07.698 --> 00:15:10.339
So is a public defender. with just as
much chance of clearing Barr.

135
00:15:10.493 --> 00:15:11.790
I'm not trying to clear him.

136
00:15:11.869 --> 00:15:14.338
I am just trying
to keep him off death row.

137
00:15:15.039 --> 00:15:17.883
- By proving he's insane?
- Well. that's one option.

138
00:15:18.126 --> 00:15:19.628
And sticking it to your father because...

139
00:15:19.710 --> 00:15:22.179
No. Not my father.
The Office of the District Attorney.

140
00:15:22.296 --> 00:15:24.977
Because the Office of the District
Attorney never bought you a pony.

141
00:15:25.967 --> 00:15:28.720
D.A. Rodin's never lost a capital case.
You know why?

142
00:15:28.886 --> 00:15:30.354
Impeccable tailoring.

143
00:15:30.471 --> 00:15:33.315
- He never picks a fight he can't win.
- Worked for the Red Baron.

144
00:15:33.391 --> 00:15:35.064
Every murder suspect in this town
is given a choice.

145
00:15:35.184 --> 00:15:36.811
Confess or face death.

146
00:15:36.978 --> 00:15:39.231
Against a D.A. who never loses.

147
00:15:39.480 --> 00:15:41.482
My firm has reason to believe
more than one innocent man

148
00:15:41.566 --> 00:15:43.068
has gone down without a fight.

149
00:15:43.651 --> 00:15:45.153
Oh. I get it.

150
00:15:46.237 --> 00:15:47.329
You're an idealist.

151
00:15:47.822 --> 00:15:49.665
No. I'm a pacifist.

152
00:15:49.907 --> 00:15:51.250
It's a noble crusade.

153
00:15:51.492 --> 00:15:55.247
But this is not the fight. Trust me.
James Barr's guilty.

154
00:15:55.413 --> 00:15:57.211
You haven't even seen the evidence.

155
00:16:01.544 --> 00:16:03.262
Is this a privileged conversation?

156
00:16:03.379 --> 00:16:07.100
Of course. it's a client conference.
Nothing you say here can be repeated.

157
00:16:09.260 --> 00:16:11.854
There are four types of people
who join the military.

158
00:16:11.929 --> 00:16:13.727
For some. it's a family trade.

159
00:16:14.223 --> 00:16:16.567
Others are patriots. eager to serve.

160
00:16:16.893 --> 00:16:18.895
Next. you have those
who just need a job.

161
00:16:19.729 --> 00:16:23.404
Then there's the kind who want a legal
means of killing other people.

162
00:16:23.900 --> 00:16:25.743
James Barr was one of those.

163
00:16:26.569 --> 00:16:28.071
<i>He made sniper.</i>

164
00:16:28.404 --> 00:16:31.408
<i>Trained hard.
Two thousand rounds a week.</i>

165
00:16:31.866 --> 00:16:33.834
<i>And with every shot.
he's taught to visualise</i>

166
00:16:33.910 --> 00:16:36.538
<i>the base of a man's skull
through his reticle.</i>

167
00:16:36.746 --> 00:16:39.590
<i>The sweet spot where
the medulla meets the spine.</i>

168
00:16:40.750 --> 00:16:43.253
<i>Visualise that puff of pink mist.</i>

169
00:16:45.087 --> 00:16:46.930
<i>Finally. he's deployed to Iraq.</i>

170
00:16:47.256 --> 00:16:48.929
<i>He's put on overwatch.</i>

171
00:16:49.550 --> 00:16:52.429
<i>All day long
he stares through a scope at civilians.</i>

172
00:16:53.095 --> 00:16:54.267
<i>Women.</i>

173
00:16:54.597 --> 00:16:55.644
<i>Children.</i>

174
00:16:56.098 --> 00:16:58.772
Day in. day out. for two long years

175
00:16:58.893 --> 00:17:01.897
without ever once being
cleared to fire a single shot.

176
00:17:02.939 --> 00:17:04.782
Then comes the drawdown.

177
00:17:05.775 --> 00:17:07.402
For James Barr. the war's over.

178
00:17:08.444 --> 00:17:10.287
<i>Two thousand rounds a week.</i>

179
00:17:10.613 --> 00:17:14.243
<i>A quarter million rounds in his career.
not one at a human target.</i>

180
00:17:15.117 --> 00:17:17.620
<i>You've been hungry.
You've been horny.</i>

181
00:17:17.954 --> 00:17:20.298
<i>You've had an itch you can't scratch.</i>

182
00:17:20.790 --> 00:17:24.795
<i>Imagine that feeling.
Days. Weeks. Years.</i>

183
00:17:25.127 --> 00:17:29.132
<i>Imagine that feeling times 200.000.
plus 50.000 more.</i>

184
00:17:29.465 --> 00:17:33.345
<i>Imagine it's 130 degrees on the deck
and tomorrow you're going home</i>

185
00:17:33.469 --> 00:17:35.437
<i>and you know if you don't
scratch that itch now.</i>

186
00:17:35.513 --> 00:17:37.140
<i>you never will.</i>

187
00:17:37.473 --> 00:17:39.146
<i>You need a release.</i>

188
00:17:39.809 --> 00:17:41.311
<i>You need a target.</i>

189
00:17:41.644 --> 00:17:44.614
<i>And the who of it
never once enters your mind.</i>

190
00:18:01.831 --> 00:18:03.833
<i>He covered his tracks well.</i>

191
00:18:03.958 --> 00:18:05.631
just like sane people do.

192
00:18:06.210 --> 00:18:10.886
He almost got away with it. too.
But I caught him. And he confessed.

193
00:18:11.132 --> 00:18:12.725
So why didn't he go to prison?

194
00:18:13.801 --> 00:18:17.180
What Barr didn't know that day was the
four civilian contractors he'd picked off

195
00:18:17.305 --> 00:18:20.559
<i>just spent the weekend
at what they call a rape-rally.</i>

196
00:18:21.142 --> 00:18:24.737
It was 28 women.
ages 54 on down to 11.

197
00:18:25.646 --> 00:18:28.820
Those were just the ones I could find
before the case was shut down.

198
00:18:29.066 --> 00:18:31.990
See. the deeper I dug. the uglier it got.

199
00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:35.665
And after seven long years
of "Mission Accomplished."

200
00:18:35.990 --> 00:18:39.335
someone in the corporation just wanted
the whole thing to end quietly.

201
00:18:39.827 --> 00:18:43.331
So they chalked it up to the fog of war.
made the murders go away.

202
00:18:43.664 --> 00:18:45.758
This is classified information.

203
00:18:47.168 --> 00:18:48.841
And that's why the privilege.

204
00:18:49.170 --> 00:18:51.172
But you were ready
to tell this to the D.A.

205
00:18:51.505 --> 00:18:55.226
The last time I saw Barr.
I made him a promise.

206
00:18:56.010 --> 00:18:59.184
And when I saw his name on the news.
I came here to keep it.

207
00:19:00.348 --> 00:19:03.067
- But now I know I don't have to.
- How can you be sure?

208
00:19:03.684 --> 00:19:05.686
You still haven't seen the evidence.

209
00:19:06.020 --> 00:19:09.741
Your father has.
And he doesn't pick a fight he can't win.

210
00:19:09.857 --> 00:19:12.406
Barr's not getting away
with murder again.

211
00:19:13.277 --> 00:19:14.369
He might.

212
00:19:15.237 --> 00:19:18.241
He suffered a severe brain injury
in state custody.

213
00:19:18.407 --> 00:19:20.125
When he wakes up. if he wakes up.

214
00:19:20.242 --> 00:19:22.961
he may not remember the event.
he may not remember anything at all.

215
00:19:24.413 --> 00:19:27.758
And this case won't be about
James Barr's guilt or innocence.

216
00:19:28.084 --> 00:19:31.088
It'll be about his ability to stand trial.

217
00:19:31.921 --> 00:19:36.392
After everything I just told you.
you still want to defend him?

218
00:19:36.467 --> 00:19:38.561
I want to see he gets a fair trial.

219
00:19:40.429 --> 00:19:43.273
You said he confessed in Baghdad.

220
00:19:43.808 --> 00:19:45.435
He didn't confess this time.

221
00:19:45.643 --> 00:19:47.924
- This time he knows better.
- This time he asked for you.

222
00:19:48.979 --> 00:19:51.198
I want to know why.

223
00:19:51.273 --> 00:19:54.322
You want to know why.
I can see it's eating you.

224
00:19:54.443 --> 00:19:55.990
And you can't ask Barr.

225
00:19:56.112 --> 00:19:58.456
and the D.A. won't let you
see the evidence.

226
00:19:59.949 --> 00:20:04.455
My lead investigator has complete
access to the evidence. All of it.

227
00:20:06.664 --> 00:20:09.504
- So where's your lead investigator?
- About to catch a bus out of town.

228
00:20:18.134 --> 00:20:20.011
Thanks for the coffee. counsellor.

229
00:21:16.025 --> 00:21:18.869
You understand you're not just
asking me to look at the evidence.

230
00:21:19.153 --> 00:21:21.747
You're asking me to look
at a cold-blooded killer.

231
00:21:21.864 --> 00:21:25.368
A man I know to be guilty.
A man you want to keep off death row.

232
00:21:25.493 --> 00:21:28.337
And you're asking me
to look at him objectively.

233
00:21:29.538 --> 00:21:31.381
Yes. that is what I'm asking.

234
00:21:36.212 --> 00:21:38.886
I'll do it. On one condition.

235
00:21:39.548 --> 00:21:40.891
Name it.

236
00:21:42.051 --> 00:21:45.396
You have to look
at the victims objectively.

237
00:21:48.432 --> 00:21:50.400
How do you suggest I do that?

238
00:21:53.562 --> 00:21:55.735
- Yes?
- Mr Farrior?

239
00:21:56.273 --> 00:21:57.900
I'm Helen Rodin.
We spoke on the phone.

240
00:21:58.901 --> 00:22:00.244
Of course.

241
00:22:00.736 --> 00:22:02.909
You said you're defending
the man that ki...

242
00:22:03.572 --> 00:22:04.573
That man.

243
00:22:05.908 --> 00:22:08.081
<i>I represent James Barr. yes.</i>

244
00:22:09.245 --> 00:22:11.247
<i>And you have questions
about my daughter?</i>

245
00:22:12.081 --> 00:22:13.424
<i>I do.</i>

246
00:22:15.251 --> 00:22:16.594
<i>What for?</i>

247
00:22:17.086 --> 00:22:20.761
I was hoping to get a better sense
of who the victims were as...

248
00:22:21.257 --> 00:22:22.858
That is to say. who they were as people.

249
00:22:22.925 --> 00:22:24.723
- As human beings.

250
00:22:29.598 --> 00:22:33.102
That's a bit unusual.
considering your position. isn't it?

251
00:22:33.435 --> 00:22:34.436
That is true.

252
00:22:35.104 --> 00:22:38.278
<i>Normally someone in my position
would want the jury</i>

253
00:22:38.440 --> 00:22:40.784
<i>to know as little as possible about the...</i>

254
00:22:41.110 --> 00:22:43.784
<i>The people that your client killed.</i>

255
00:22:44.780 --> 00:22:46.123
<i>In cold blood.</i>

256
00:22:52.246 --> 00:22:53.998
Have you spoken
with the other families?

257
00:22:54.123 --> 00:22:57.252
Yeah. some.
The ones who would speak with me.

258
00:23:06.635 --> 00:23:08.012
Come in.

259
00:23:08.137 --> 00:23:09.480
Thank you.

260
00:25:08.924 --> 00:25:10.767
<i>Chrissie was a nanny.</i>

261
00:25:11.385 --> 00:25:13.058
She had a little girl with her that day.

262
00:25:13.387 --> 00:25:14.434
Yes. I know.

263
00:25:17.391 --> 00:25:19.769
Are you gonna go talk with that child?

264
00:25:20.102 --> 00:25:21.775
No. of course not. I...

265
00:25:22.938 --> 00:25:23.939
Why not?

266
00:25:24.231 --> 00:25:26.905
- Well. I think it would be...
- Insensitive?

267
00:25:28.444 --> 00:25:29.616
Inappropriate?

268
00:25:32.948 --> 00:25:35.792
Everything that you want to know
about my daughter

269
00:25:38.120 --> 00:25:39.121
is right here.

270
00:25:41.290 --> 00:25:43.463
The<i> Gazette</i> did a nice piece on her.

271
00:25:45.586 --> 00:25:47.930
Her obituary does the rest.

272
00:25:51.133 --> 00:25:54.603
Thank you. I'll definitely have a look.

273
00:25:55.304 --> 00:25:57.306
You a good attorney. Miss Rodin?

274
00:25:58.265 --> 00:26:00.643
- That's not really for me to...
- Just

275
00:26:01.101 --> 00:26:02.444
answer the question.

276
00:26:03.479 --> 00:26:06.983
Yes. I suppose I am pretty good.

277
00:26:07.274 --> 00:26:09.151
Good enough to keep
that man off death row?

278
00:26:10.319 --> 00:26:11.662
You know.

279
00:26:12.112 --> 00:26:13.455
I think maybe I should go.

280
00:26:13.655 --> 00:26:15.157
You stay where you are.

281
00:26:20.496 --> 00:26:22.840
That man deserves to die. Miss Rodin.

282
00:26:26.335 --> 00:26:28.133
Why would you defend him?

283
00:26:28.337 --> 00:26:31.341
I can see
that I have made a terrible mistake.

284
00:26:32.508 --> 00:26:36.513
And I'm very. very sorry
and I promise I won't bother you again.

285
00:26:47.856 --> 00:26:49.278
Hello. Dad.

286
00:26:49.358 --> 00:26:50.701
What the hell are you doing?

287
00:26:51.026 --> 00:26:52.369
What am I... What?

288
00:26:52.528 --> 00:26:53.529
Is it true?

289
00:26:53.695 --> 00:26:55.735
You're talking to the victims' families?
You? Alone?

290
00:26:56.824 --> 00:26:58.747
How do you know that?
How did you find me here?

291
00:26:58.867 --> 00:27:01.120
I'm the District Attorney.
It's my business to know.

292
00:27:01.203 --> 00:27:02.250
That's not an answer.

293
00:27:02.371 --> 00:27:06.547
Oh. Well. you're not the only one
with crack investigators. Helen.

294
00:27:06.875 --> 00:27:09.378
That's right. I know about Reacher.

295
00:27:09.711 --> 00:27:12.055
Your lead investigator is a war veteran

296
00:27:12.172 --> 00:27:14.721
who's been missing
for the last two years.

297
00:27:15.509 --> 00:27:17.637
How can you vouch
for his state of mind?

298
00:27:17.719 --> 00:27:19.062
How can you trust anything he tells you?

299
00:27:19.179 --> 00:27:20.396
You don't know the man.

300
00:27:21.723 --> 00:27:24.727
Tell me this.
does he know you can't pay him?

301
00:27:25.060 --> 00:27:27.233
That your own firm
didn't want this case?

302
00:27:27.354 --> 00:27:29.573
That nobody wants this case?

303
00:27:30.566 --> 00:27:33.536
You never even spoke to your client
before he wound up in a coma.

304
00:27:33.735 --> 00:27:36.335
Oh. now listen to me! Listen.
Listen. I'm speaking as your father.

305
00:27:36.572 --> 00:27:38.449
Whatever our differences
have been in the past.

306
00:27:38.574 --> 00:27:40.247
you gotta listen to me now.

307
00:27:42.244 --> 00:27:44.588
You're making a terrible mistake.

308
00:27:45.080 --> 00:27:47.424
You cannot win this case.

309
00:27:48.417 --> 00:27:51.421
You're going to ruin your career.
Why? For what?

310
00:27:52.421 --> 00:27:55.425
To hurt me? To change me?

311
00:27:55.591 --> 00:27:57.264
- Helen...
- Don't touch me!

312
00:28:09.563 --> 00:28:11.243
Thanks for letting me take a look.

313
00:28:11.398 --> 00:28:13.275
Hey. We love it
when friends of the accused

314
00:28:13.442 --> 00:28:15.069
try to tear our work to shreds.

315
00:28:15.277 --> 00:28:16.620
He's not my friend.

316
00:28:16.778 --> 00:28:19.782
So you keep saying. Find any holes?

317
00:28:20.115 --> 00:28:22.288
Well. you didn't have to
put him in the hospital.

318
00:28:23.118 --> 00:28:26.463
Other than that. damn fine police work.
It's open and shut.

319
00:28:27.956 --> 00:28:30.175
What can I say?
The scene was a gold mine.

320
00:28:30.292 --> 00:28:33.796
Come on. Now we both know
gold's only as good as the man digging.

321
00:28:33.921 --> 00:28:36.800
Yeah. well. anytime you want to come
back. take a look at this stuff...

322
00:28:36.924 --> 00:28:38.642
No. thanks. Don't need to.

323
00:28:38.967 --> 00:28:40.469
You never took any notes.

324
00:28:41.970 --> 00:28:43.142
Oh. I don't need to.

325
00:28:44.932 --> 00:28:48.311
So you were some real hot shit
in the Army. huh?

326
00:28:48.936 --> 00:28:50.279
I did all right.

327
00:28:50.646 --> 00:28:53.320
So what does an Army cop do mostly?
Break up bar fights?

328
00:28:53.815 --> 00:28:56.819
I did what you do pretty much.
with one minor difference.

329
00:28:56.985 --> 00:28:57.986
What's that?

330
00:28:58.487 --> 00:29:00.831
Every suspect was a trained killer.

331
00:29:01.782 --> 00:29:03.125
Thanks again.

332
00:29:09.331 --> 00:29:11.174
Why do you think he paid for parking?

333
00:29:13.669 --> 00:29:14.795
Pardon?

334
00:29:14.962 --> 00:29:18.683
He's about to fire six shots
into a crowd of strangers.

335
00:29:19.174 --> 00:29:21.176
And he's worried about the meter maid?

336
00:29:21.343 --> 00:29:23.016
"Simple loony" won't do it for you?

337
00:29:23.303 --> 00:29:25.351
I like to have
at least one alternate theory.

338
00:29:26.640 --> 00:29:27.687
Huh.

339
00:29:28.517 --> 00:29:29.689
Habit.

340
00:29:30.352 --> 00:29:31.695
Muscle memory.

341
00:29:32.354 --> 00:29:34.356
I don't think he knew he was doing it.

342
00:29:36.358 --> 00:29:38.702
Like I said. it's damn fine work.

343
00:29:38.986 --> 00:29:40.033
Hey. Army.

344
00:29:41.697 --> 00:29:43.699
What's the serial number on the rifle?

345
00:29:48.036 --> 00:29:49.276
What's the date on the quarter?

346
00:29:52.374 --> 00:29:53.546
1968.

347
00:29:57.045 --> 00:29:58.718
Forest for the trees. Detective.

348
00:29:59.881 --> 00:30:01.724
Forest for the trees.

349
00:31:15.707 --> 00:31:17.380
Mind if I share your table?

350
00:31:19.378 --> 00:31:20.470
I'm Sandy.

351
00:31:21.129 --> 00:31:23.632
So was I. Last week.

352
00:31:24.716 --> 00:31:26.468
On a beach. in Florida.

353
00:31:30.472 --> 00:31:31.564
What's your name?

354
00:31:33.558 --> 00:31:34.980
Jimmie Reese.

355
00:31:37.729 --> 00:31:39.572
You don't look like a Jimmie.

356
00:31:39.648 --> 00:31:40.695
What do I look like?

357
00:31:42.651 --> 00:31:45.495
I don't know. But not a Jimmie.

358
00:31:45.904 --> 00:31:46.996
Hmm.

359
00:31:47.072 --> 00:31:48.915
So you're new in town?

360
00:31:49.658 --> 00:31:51.001
Usually.

361
00:31:51.326 --> 00:31:53.499
It's kind of loud in here.

362
00:31:54.162 --> 00:31:57.837
Do you want to maybe go
someplace quieter? I have a car.

363
00:31:58.083 --> 00:31:59.505
You're old enough to drive?

364
00:32:00.419 --> 00:32:02.763
I'm old enough to do a lot of things.

365
00:32:03.839 --> 00:32:05.682
I'm on a budget. Sandy.

366
00:32:06.174 --> 00:32:07.266
What?

367
00:32:07.509 --> 00:32:08.852
I can't afford you.

368
00:32:09.344 --> 00:32:10.516
I'm not a hooker.

369
00:32:10.929 --> 00:32:13.182
Oh. then I really can't afford you.

370
00:32:13.348 --> 00:32:16.022
Seriously. I work at the auto parts store.

371
00:32:17.102 --> 00:32:20.697
What I mean is. the cheapest woman
tends to be the one you pay for.

372
00:32:23.108 --> 00:32:24.701
I am not a hooker!

373
00:32:24.860 --> 00:32:26.362
No. A hooker would get the joke.

374
00:32:26.611 --> 00:32:29.535
- What's this?
- He called me a whore.

375
00:32:33.535 --> 00:32:34.707
Is that true?

376
00:32:38.540 --> 00:32:42.215
Well. nobody said whore.
She inferred hooker. but I meant slut.

377
00:32:42.461 --> 00:32:44.213
Hey. That's our sister.

378
00:32:45.213 --> 00:32:46.556
Is she a good kisser?

379
00:32:47.883 --> 00:32:49.556
Hey. Outside.

380
00:32:50.719 --> 00:32:52.392
Pay your cheque first.

381
00:32:52.554 --> 00:32:53.555
I'll pay later.

382
00:32:54.806 --> 00:32:56.228
You won't be able to.

383
00:32:56.641 --> 00:32:57.733
You think?

384
00:32:57.893 --> 00:32:59.395
All the time. You should try it.

385
00:33:00.228 --> 00:33:01.980
It's a great joke.
but I'm going to beat your ass.

386
00:33:02.063 --> 00:33:03.815
Do you want to do that here or outside?

387
00:33:09.070 --> 00:33:10.413
Outside.

388
00:33:13.658 --> 00:33:15.331
Stay here. Sandy.

389
00:33:16.578 --> 00:33:18.330
I don't mind the sight of blood.

390
00:33:19.581 --> 00:33:22.084
When it means
you're not pregnant. anyway.

391
00:33:40.519 --> 00:33:42.772
You still think you're funny now. creep?

392
00:33:42.938 --> 00:33:45.441
Shut your mouth. Sandy!
No one is talking to you.

393
00:33:52.614 --> 00:33:54.366
It's your last chance to walk away.

394
00:33:56.117 --> 00:33:58.119
Are you kidding? It's five against one.

395
00:34:00.038 --> 00:34:01.130
It's three against one.

396
00:34:02.791 --> 00:34:04.464
How do you figure?

397
00:34:04.709 --> 00:34:07.383
Well. once I take out the leader.
which is you.

398
00:34:07.629 --> 00:34:11.304
I'll have to contend
with one or two enthusiastic wingmen.

399
00:34:11.883 --> 00:34:14.807
The last two guys. they always run.

400
00:34:15.053 --> 00:34:16.646
Oh. you've done this before?

401
00:34:16.721 --> 00:34:18.223
Yeah.

402
00:34:20.141 --> 00:34:21.643
It's getting late.

403
00:34:24.312 --> 00:34:25.404
Remember.

404
00:34:26.147 --> 00:34:27.569
you wanted this.

405
00:34:33.822 --> 00:34:36.120
It's okay. You're okay.

406
00:34:36.199 --> 00:34:38.076
- Get up.

407
00:34:47.502 --> 00:34:48.503
Okay.

408
00:34:48.587 --> 00:34:50.260
Now we know who's who.

409
00:34:50.589 --> 00:34:51.932
Let's get this done.

410
00:35:08.690 --> 00:35:09.862
Really?

411
00:35:13.612 --> 00:35:15.535
Shit!

412
00:35:23.538 --> 00:35:24.881
On the ground!

413
00:35:25.040 --> 00:35:26.963
That's a pretty impressive
response time. fellas.

414
00:35:27.208 --> 00:35:28.380
Do it!

415
00:35:36.384 --> 00:35:37.727
Hands behind your back.

416
00:35:40.889 --> 00:35:42.061
Who hired you?

417
00:35:44.225 --> 00:35:45.397
Let's go.

418
00:36:01.242 --> 00:36:02.334
Hey. Helen.

419
00:36:02.577 --> 00:36:04.420
Am I wearing too much perfume?

420
00:36:05.330 --> 00:36:08.425
Breathing too sternly.
Detective Emerson.

421
00:36:08.750 --> 00:36:11.253
- Somebody dead?
- And if someone is?

422
00:36:13.254 --> 00:36:16.258
Then they died of shame.
'Cause I was being gentle.

423
00:36:16.341 --> 00:36:19.595
I'm starting to understand
why you move around a lot. Reacher.

424
00:36:20.011 --> 00:36:21.684
So no one's dead.

425
00:36:22.013 --> 00:36:24.607
One guy
likely won't ever walk right again.

426
00:36:24.766 --> 00:36:27.110
- You want to charge me.
- Very much.

427
00:36:27.352 --> 00:36:28.444
But no one's pressing.

428
00:36:28.937 --> 00:36:30.280
Sadly. no.

429
00:36:34.025 --> 00:36:35.368
Am I free to go?

430
00:36:37.946 --> 00:36:39.118
Hey. Emerson.

431
00:36:44.119 --> 00:36:45.792
4862681.

432
00:36:47.455 --> 00:36:48.627
What's that?

433
00:36:48.873 --> 00:36:51.717
It's the serial number on Barr's rifle.

434
00:36:57.465 --> 00:36:59.467
You're working for me.
do you understand that?

435
00:36:59.718 --> 00:37:03.643
So everything you do
is a reflection on my firm. On me.

436
00:37:03.805 --> 00:37:04.806
I was set up.

437
00:37:04.973 --> 00:37:06.065
You're talking to a lawyer.

438
00:37:06.141 --> 00:37:09.065
There was this girl. She came onto me.
Picked a fight.

439
00:37:09.144 --> 00:37:10.737
Which never happens in a bar.

440
00:37:10.895 --> 00:37:12.897
She was thrown
when I told her my name.

441
00:37:13.064 --> 00:37:14.224
She was expecting Mike Tyson?

442
00:37:14.315 --> 00:37:15.988
She wasn't expecting Jimmie Reese.

443
00:37:18.319 --> 00:37:19.741
Yankees second baseman.

444
00:37:20.321 --> 00:37:22.281
Why did you say you were
a Yankees second baseman?

445
00:37:23.491 --> 00:37:25.164
I always use Yankees second basemen.

446
00:37:25.243 --> 00:37:28.497
I didn't say I was a Yankees
second baseman. I just said...

447
00:37:29.497 --> 00:37:32.171
Look. the point is.

448
00:37:32.250 --> 00:37:34.173
she was expecting to hear
"Jack Reacher."

449
00:37:34.335 --> 00:37:35.427
She knew who I was.

450
00:37:35.503 --> 00:37:37.505
And the cops were rolling
before the fight even started.

451
00:37:37.672 --> 00:37:40.516
And those five guys are her brothers?
Come on.

452
00:37:41.509 --> 00:37:44.183
Someone sent those boys
to put me down.

453
00:37:46.347 --> 00:37:47.519
Who?

454
00:37:50.518 --> 00:37:52.646
If someone followed you
at the river today.

455
00:37:52.729 --> 00:37:54.527
it was probably a cop.
And I highly doubt...

456
00:37:54.606 --> 00:37:56.108
There are three things cops never do.

457
00:37:56.357 --> 00:37:58.860
They don't vote Democrat.
they don't drive Cadillacs.

458
00:37:58.943 --> 00:38:01.116
and they never use personal vehicles.

459
00:38:02.530 --> 00:38:03.622
It's not a cop.

460
00:38:03.782 --> 00:38:05.876
A P.I.. then. or the D.A.'s office.

461
00:38:05.950 --> 00:38:07.791
You think your father's office
would set me up?

462
00:38:07.869 --> 00:38:09.121
Why would anyone set you up?

463
00:38:09.204 --> 00:38:10.456
How was your day?

464
00:38:10.538 --> 00:38:12.040
It went exactly the way I think

465
00:38:13.041 --> 00:38:14.793
you hoped it would.

466
00:38:16.878 --> 00:38:17.925
You Okay?

467
00:38:19.047 --> 00:38:20.094
Mmm-hmm.

468
00:38:21.633 --> 00:38:22.805
What'd you learn?

469
00:38:25.804 --> 00:38:28.307
<i>Chrissie Farrior was 22.</i>

470
00:38:29.474 --> 00:38:33.320
<i>A nanny caring for the six-year-old
daughter of family friends.</i>

471
00:38:34.813 --> 00:38:37.407
She'd finally saved enough
money for a trip to China.

472
00:38:37.482 --> 00:38:39.610
in fact. she should have left
the week before.

473
00:38:39.984 --> 00:38:44.160
<i>But the girl she cared for wanted
Chrissie to stay for her 7th birthday.</i>

474
00:38:45.323 --> 00:38:48.668
<i>They'd gone downtown that day
to shop for a party dress.</i>

475
00:38:52.163 --> 00:38:56.339
<i>Rita Coronado worked as a cleaning
lady at the River Cross Plaza.</i>

476
00:38:57.085 --> 00:38:59.929
She was usually late for work.
but she had a good reason.

477
00:39:00.672 --> 00:39:02.470
<i>Since her son Marco
was nine years old</i>

478
00:39:02.590 --> 00:39:06.561
<i>she had to personally drop him at
school to make sure he actually went.</i>

479
00:39:06.636 --> 00:39:08.809
<i>But her dedication had paid off.</i>

480
00:39:09.347 --> 00:39:11.691
<i>Marco was now an honour student.</i>

481
00:39:12.100 --> 00:39:13.977
<i>As a reward for all his hard work.</i>

482
00:39:14.102 --> 00:39:16.275
<i>Rita was taking him
to his first baseball game.</i>

483
00:39:17.021 --> 00:39:20.321
<i>And she was on her way to pick up
the tickets that very afternoon.</i>

484
00:39:22.694 --> 00:39:25.368
<i>Nancy Holt's last words to her husband
were</i> a <i>lie.</i>

485
00:39:25.697 --> 00:39:27.290
- I love you. babe. See you!
- Bye.

486
00:39:27.365 --> 00:39:29.208
She told him she was
taking her car to be serviced.

487
00:39:29.284 --> 00:39:31.537
but in fact. she was headed downtown.

488
00:39:34.706 --> 00:39:35.753
It's perfect.

489
00:39:35.832 --> 00:39:38.912
<i>She told the clerk she didn't want the
purchase showing up on her credit card.</i>

490
00:39:39.210 --> 00:39:42.134
<i>She wanted to surprise her
husband for their 10th anniversary</i>

491
00:39:43.631 --> 00:39:45.633
<i>- just a few days away.</i>
- Thank you.

492
00:39:47.719 --> 00:39:51.223
<i>Oline Archer never liked
her husband's construction business.</i>

493
00:39:51.556 --> 00:39:56.062
<i>even after helping him become one of
the largest contractors in the county.</i>

494
00:39:56.561 --> 00:40:00.611
<i>So it came as a relief when
his failing health and a costly lawsuit</i>

495
00:40:00.690 --> 00:40:02.488
<i>were forcing them
to sell to the competition.</i>

496
00:40:02.734 --> 00:40:03.826
Rob?

497
00:40:04.319 --> 00:40:05.696
Help! Help!

498
00:40:08.323 --> 00:40:11.327
<i>Her husband
had given his life for the company.</i>

499
00:40:12.243 --> 00:40:14.245
<i>But now that it was hers.</i>

500
00:40:14.746 --> 00:40:16.840
<i>she couldn't bring herself to let it go.</i>

501
00:40:22.420 --> 00:40:25.094
<i>She was on her way
to secure a loan that day</i>

502
00:40:25.340 --> 00:40:28.435
<i>so she could keep the business
she'd always hated.</i>

503
00:40:29.427 --> 00:40:31.600
<i>Darren Sawyer was
an investment broker</i>

504
00:40:31.679 --> 00:40:33.773
<i>in the same building where Rita worked.</i>

505
00:40:34.015 --> 00:40:37.110
<i>His wife said
he'd grown increasingly distant of late.</i>

506
00:40:37.352 --> 00:40:42.028
<i>She can't remember their last words
to one another. but they weren't kind.</i>

507
00:40:42.440 --> 00:40:44.693
<i>Darren's body was found beside
a fresh bouquet of roses</i>

508
00:40:44.776 --> 00:40:46.778
<i>he'd bought that morning</i>

509
00:40:46.945 --> 00:40:50.290
<i>and his wife takes comfort
in the fact that. in his last moments.</i>

510
00:40:50.531 --> 00:40:52.954
<i>he was most likely thinking of her.</i>

511
00:41:12.804 --> 00:41:15.023
We're gonna be okay.
We're gonna be okay.

512
00:41:15.098 --> 00:41:16.475
We're gonna be okay.

513
00:41:16.808 --> 00:41:18.560
We're gonna be okay.
we're gonna be okay.

514
00:41:18.643 --> 00:41:20.244
we're gonna be okay.
we're gonna be okay.

515
00:41:32.907 --> 00:41:34.250
So what'd you learn?

516
00:41:35.660 --> 00:41:37.162
You want me to say you were right.

517
00:41:37.245 --> 00:41:39.122
You want me to say
that this isn't the fight.

518
00:41:40.164 --> 00:41:41.837
James Barr should die.

519
00:41:43.418 --> 00:41:44.465
Maybe he should.

520
00:41:44.669 --> 00:41:46.470
I meant. what did you
learn about the victims.

521
00:41:46.504 --> 00:41:47.551
What more do you want?

522
00:41:47.630 --> 00:41:49.849
They were five innocent people
senselessly murdered.

523
00:41:49.924 --> 00:41:51.926
I'm sorry.
Could you please put a shirt on?

524
00:41:52.343 --> 00:41:53.515
This is my shirt.

525
00:41:55.013 --> 00:41:56.105
You lose your luggage?

526
00:41:56.264 --> 00:41:57.766
I don't have any luggage.

527
00:41:58.933 --> 00:42:00.685
Uh. what was I saying?

528
00:42:00.852 --> 00:42:03.355
- Five innocent people.
- Murdered at random. yes.

529
00:42:06.357 --> 00:42:09.110
You know how many people
die in this country every year?

530
00:42:09.610 --> 00:42:10.782
Two and a half million.

531
00:42:12.113 --> 00:42:13.205
That means every day.

532
00:42:13.364 --> 00:42:17.119
roughly 7.000 average Americans
wake up for the last time.

533
00:42:17.452 --> 00:42:20.501
Last Friday. five of them converged
on a single spot and died together.

534
00:42:20.621 --> 00:42:21.622
Is that random?

535
00:42:21.706 --> 00:42:23.128
What else would you call it?

536
00:42:23.207 --> 00:42:26.427
Well. take Darren and Nancy.
Odds are they were having an affair.

537
00:42:26.502 --> 00:42:27.549
Excuse me?

538
00:42:27.628 --> 00:42:30.347
You don't buy roses
for your wife on the way to work.

539
00:42:30.465 --> 00:42:32.138
<i>You buy them on the way home.</i>

540
00:42:33.217 --> 00:42:35.811
And you don't worry about a charge
showing up on your credit card

541
00:42:35.887 --> 00:42:37.639
when your anniversary is that weekend.

542
00:42:38.056 --> 00:42:39.979
<i>Unless it's the gift you're hiding.</i>

543
00:42:43.644 --> 00:42:45.021
And that's why she kept walking

544
00:42:47.398 --> 00:42:49.400
while everyone else ran.

545
00:42:49.650 --> 00:42:50.993
You can't prove that.

546
00:42:51.235 --> 00:42:54.580
How hard would it be?
Cell phones. e-mails.

547
00:42:56.574 --> 00:42:58.668
All it takes is someone willing to dig.

548
00:42:58.826 --> 00:43:00.828
What's your point exactly?

549
00:43:00.912 --> 00:43:04.416
My point is that two of the victims
weren't there strictly by chance.

550
00:43:06.417 --> 00:43:08.260
I need a list of Barr's known associates.

551
00:43:08.419 --> 00:43:10.513
There isn't one. He didn't have any.

552
00:43:10.588 --> 00:43:12.761
He's a classic loner.
He didn't even talk to his neighbours.

553
00:43:12.840 --> 00:43:15.263
He was a quiet man.
Never bothered anyone.

554
00:43:15.343 --> 00:43:16.686
Yeah. exactly.

555
00:43:16.761 --> 00:43:19.935
- You have his credit card statement?
- I can get it. Why?

556
00:43:20.014 --> 00:43:22.312
I need the list
of all the places he hung out.

557
00:43:22.391 --> 00:43:24.860
Bars. bowling alleys. strip clubs.

558
00:43:25.728 --> 00:43:26.775
gun ranges.

559
00:43:27.105 --> 00:43:28.652
Anywhere someone
would remember him.

560
00:43:28.731 --> 00:43:29.903
What do we hope to find?

561
00:43:30.942 --> 00:43:32.194
I need some sleep.

562
00:43:33.444 --> 00:43:34.787
You. too.

563
00:43:35.530 --> 00:43:36.930
You don't really think I'm gonna...

564
00:43:43.621 --> 00:43:45.623
Be back to pick me up at 7:00.

565
00:43:49.293 --> 00:43:51.387
Yep. Absolutely.

566
00:44:31.502 --> 00:44:32.845
Who's with you?

567
00:44:33.087 --> 00:44:34.509
What happened?

568
00:44:35.673 --> 00:44:37.346
Oh. that's him. isn't it?

569
00:44:38.176 --> 00:44:39.519
I ain't seeing you. man!

570
00:44:39.760 --> 00:44:41.433
Relax. What happened?

571
00:44:43.014 --> 00:44:45.312
Barr's attorney hired an investigator.

572
00:44:45.683 --> 00:44:48.527
Name of Reacher.
Some sort of top-shelf Army cop.

573
00:44:48.603 --> 00:44:50.697
He was in Baghdad
the same time as Barr.

574
00:44:51.355 --> 00:44:52.527
So?

575
00:44:54.150 --> 00:44:56.369
So Barr asked for this soldier by name.

576
00:44:56.444 --> 00:44:59.323
Then he shows up at the river today.
Then up on the highway.

577
00:44:59.530 --> 00:45:01.203
Almost like he knew something.

578
00:45:02.533 --> 00:45:04.706
And you said we don't like
people asking questions.

579
00:45:04.785 --> 00:45:06.207
No. we sure don't.

580
00:45:06.454 --> 00:45:07.797
So I took steps.

581
00:45:09.207 --> 00:45:10.880
You took steps.

582
00:45:11.209 --> 00:45:13.382
Local people. My guys.

583
00:45:13.711 --> 00:45:15.304
And it blew back on you.

584
00:45:16.214 --> 00:45:17.932
I figured five guys would do it.

585
00:45:18.007 --> 00:45:21.056
Mmm. This franchise
was yours to manage.

586
00:45:21.385 --> 00:45:24.229
That's all. Maintenance is our thing.
you understand?

587
00:45:24.305 --> 00:45:25.352
Yeah. I understand. I couldn't reach you!

588
00:45:25.473 --> 00:45:26.474
Well. that's how this works.

589
00:45:26.557 --> 00:45:27.900
Well. I had to make a decision!

590
00:45:28.142 --> 00:45:30.691
- These locals. I want their names.
- It's in the file.

591
00:45:30.895 --> 00:45:32.055
Any of them know who you are?

592
00:45:32.563 --> 00:45:34.156
Just one. but I took care of it.

593
00:45:35.566 --> 00:45:36.658
You...

594
00:45:37.401 --> 00:45:39.529
- Where's the body?
- It's distributed.

595
00:45:40.738 --> 00:45:41.785
Relax! No one's gonna find it.

596
00:45:41.864 --> 00:45:44.162
- Suppose we want it found. yeah?
- Why the hell would you want it found?

597
00:45:44.242 --> 00:45:47.246
'Cause we got a way of doing things
so they stay done.

598
00:45:47.745 --> 00:45:49.088
Clean!

599
00:45:49.664 --> 00:45:51.211
A missing person isn't clean.

600
00:45:51.415 --> 00:45:53.815
Christ's sakes. man. You only had to kill
one goddamn person.

601
00:45:53.834 --> 00:45:55.314
You tapped five! You call that clean?

602
00:45:55.336 --> 00:45:59.512
I call it done. They're looking
at the shooter. not the target.

603
00:45:59.674 --> 00:46:00.766
Jesus.

604
00:46:01.092 --> 00:46:04.847
We make it messy now
so it won't get messy later.

605
00:46:04.929 --> 00:46:08.103
And we don't leave
questions unanswered ever.

606
00:46:08.432 --> 00:46:11.276
Okay. all right. Okay. I can fix this.

607
00:46:11.686 --> 00:46:14.030
- Open your eyes.
- No. I ain't seeing you!

608
00:46:14.272 --> 00:46:16.115
It makes no difference now.

609
00:46:25.449 --> 00:46:27.122
I made a mistake.

610
00:46:27.952 --> 00:46:29.875
I mean. you can still use me.
just tell me how to fix...

611
00:46:29.954 --> 00:46:33.800
To survive.
Don't say "fix it." because you can't.

612
00:46:34.125 --> 00:46:37.129
We covered up the one mess.
You made another.

613
00:46:37.295 --> 00:46:38.968
All right. You're right.

614
00:46:39.046 --> 00:46:40.548
You're right.
You're absolutely right. I'm sorry.

615
00:46:40.631 --> 00:46:43.305
Just tell me what I have to do.

616
00:46:44.552 --> 00:46:47.055
I was in prison in Siberia.

617
00:46:47.471 --> 00:46:51.146
I spent my first winter
wearing a dead man's coat.

618
00:46:51.475 --> 00:46:53.648
A hole in one pocket.

619
00:46:54.145 --> 00:46:55.988
I chewed these fingers off

620
00:46:56.063 --> 00:46:59.158
before the frostbite
could turn to gangrene.

621
00:47:01.319 --> 00:47:05.165
These I gave up
to avoid working in the sulphur mine.

622
00:47:06.490 --> 00:47:09.994
That is how I survived
when so many others did not.

623
00:47:11.495 --> 00:47:14.669
A man this rare can always be of use.

624
00:47:16.000 --> 00:47:19.174
So show me. Show me you are rare.

625
00:47:20.004 --> 00:47:22.427
Show me you'll do anything to survive.

626
00:47:24.008 --> 00:47:25.476
I don't understand.

627
00:47:25.843 --> 00:47:28.517
The fingers from your left hand.

628
00:47:53.871 --> 00:47:57.341
Have you... Have you got a knife?

629
00:47:57.541 --> 00:48:00.135
Did I have a knife in Siberia?

630
00:48:02.880 --> 00:48:06.475
No... Come on. you've got to be kidding.

631
00:48:07.218 --> 00:48:08.640
You can do it.

632
00:48:09.053 --> 00:48:10.396
Show me.

633
00:48:42.253 --> 00:48:43.596
Christ!

634
00:48:44.588 --> 00:48:46.886
Can't! I can't.

635
00:48:47.091 --> 00:48:49.139
Always the bullet.

636
00:48:49.218 --> 00:48:50.891
- I can't!
- I don't understand.

637
00:48:58.102 --> 00:48:59.775
What do we do about the soldier?

638
00:49:00.438 --> 00:49:02.065
What we always do.

639
00:49:08.279 --> 00:49:10.828
Barr's credit card statement.
Eyewitness testimonies.

640
00:49:11.449 --> 00:49:14.293
Coffee. You take it black. right?

641
00:49:20.291 --> 00:49:22.635
Yeah. What can I say?
I take my work home.

642
00:49:36.432 --> 00:49:39.106
Afraid Barr's credit card
statement's a dead end.

643
00:49:40.936 --> 00:49:44.065
No bars. no strip joints. nothing.
Pretty much just gas and groceries.

644
00:49:46.150 --> 00:49:49.620
I need you to look for gun ranges
between 100 and 150 miles from here.

645
00:49:50.154 --> 00:49:52.657
Limit your search to ranges
longer than 300 yards.

646
00:49:52.781 --> 00:49:54.078
Sure. if you tell me why.

647
00:49:54.158 --> 00:49:56.661
Barr consistently filled
his tank on Saturday.

648
00:49:56.785 --> 00:49:58.002
and again on Sunday.

649
00:49:58.120 --> 00:49:59.760
He took a long drive
almost every weekend.

650
00:49:59.997 --> 00:50:02.091
- He could be going anywhere.
- Yes.

651
00:50:03.000 --> 00:50:06.174
And if it's bars. bowling alleys
or strip clubs. we'll never find it.

652
00:50:06.504 --> 00:50:09.633
But a Match-level gun range?
There might be two.

653
00:50:10.007 --> 00:50:13.511
And he made his own bullets.
That means he shot a lot.

654
00:50:14.345 --> 00:50:16.018
I'm guessing every Saturday.

655
00:50:17.181 --> 00:50:18.603
Maybe with a friend.

656
00:50:18.807 --> 00:50:21.435
Why is it so important
you talk to his friends?

657
00:50:21.519 --> 00:50:22.645
Assuming he had any.

658
00:50:22.853 --> 00:50:24.355
Drop me at the auto parts store.

659
00:50:24.480 --> 00:50:26.323
I... Wait. Which one?

660
00:50:26.857 --> 00:50:28.859
I don't know.
She just said "the auto parts store."

661
00:50:28.943 --> 00:50:29.990
She? Who?

662
00:50:30.110 --> 00:50:31.612
Reacher. can you be
a little more specific?

663
00:50:31.695 --> 00:50:34.039
I didn't say "an auto parts store."

664
00:50:34.365 --> 00:50:37.665
Which one stands out in your mind
as the auto parts store?

665
00:50:47.378 --> 00:50:48.880
You want me to wait?

666
00:50:50.005 --> 00:50:53.126
- No. I'll meet you back at the office later.
- How will you get there?

667
00:50:56.720 --> 00:50:58.188
I'll hitch a ride.

668
00:51:40.764 --> 00:51:41.936
Can I help you?

669
00:51:42.266 --> 00:51:43.313
Sandy work here?

670
00:51:45.644 --> 00:51:46.691
What's this about?

671
00:51:47.438 --> 00:51:49.941
So she does. thanks.
I need to speak with her.

672
00:51:50.065 --> 00:51:51.442
It's a personal matter.

673
00:51:52.067 --> 00:51:54.911
- She's on the clock.
- Legal personal matter.

674
00:51:56.071 --> 00:51:57.243
What are you. a cop?

675
00:51:58.782 --> 00:52:00.409
Call her out. Gary.

676
00:52:00.743 --> 00:52:03.087
- I'm gonna need to see some I.D.
- Go get Sandy.

677
00:52:03.621 --> 00:52:05.623
Well. I need to see something.

678
00:52:06.290 --> 00:52:08.759
How about the inside of an ambulance?

679
00:52:11.962 --> 00:52:14.761
Okay. I'm calling the police.

680
00:52:17.468 --> 00:52:19.470
I don't think Sandy wants
the police involved...

681
00:52:19.595 --> 00:52:20.812
- Hello?
...but let's ask.

682
00:52:21.055 --> 00:52:22.102
Hey! You...

683
00:52:22.306 --> 00:52:25.310
Hello? I need some help.
Hello? Hey! You!

684
00:52:26.477 --> 00:52:29.356
No. You are not allowed
back in here. man!

685
00:52:35.444 --> 00:52:36.616
Shit.

686
00:52:39.990 --> 00:52:41.333
You know this guy?

687
00:52:41.617 --> 00:52:42.664
Tell him.

688
00:52:43.952 --> 00:52:45.295
Give us a few. Gary.

689
00:52:57.007 --> 00:53:00.056
Listen. I wasn't... I didn't know.

690
00:53:00.177 --> 00:53:02.726
I didn't know that was going to happen!

691
00:53:08.519 --> 00:53:09.566
It was Jeb.

692
00:53:10.979 --> 00:53:12.356
The big guy.

693
00:53:12.690 --> 00:53:14.363
Jeb Oliver.

694
00:53:17.194 --> 00:53:21.665
He told me you were a predator.
You were supposed to star groping me.

695
00:53:28.205 --> 00:53:29.673
Just don't hurt me.

696
00:53:30.040 --> 00:53:32.213
Sandy. sit down.

697
00:53:35.254 --> 00:53:36.346
Where can I find Jeb?

698
00:53:36.880 --> 00:53:38.560
I don't know.
He didn't come to work today.

699
00:53:38.590 --> 00:53:39.887
So he works here.

700
00:53:40.384 --> 00:53:41.556
Yeah.

701
00:53:42.886 --> 00:53:45.560
It's bullshit. though. He cooks crystal.

702
00:53:45.681 --> 00:53:47.103
His address. write it down.

703
00:53:50.394 --> 00:53:51.896
I'm really sorry. mister.

704
00:53:53.230 --> 00:53:55.574
You were supposed to be a pervert.

705
00:53:57.234 --> 00:53:59.236
And it was an easy 100 bucks.

706
00:53:59.528 --> 00:54:00.575
That's all?

707
00:54:02.906 --> 00:54:06.706
When Jeb asks. you do what he says.

708
00:54:11.248 --> 00:54:12.591
Am I in trouble?

709
00:54:15.711 --> 00:54:17.429
Not if you lend me your car.

710
00:54:18.213 --> 00:54:20.636
- I don't have a car.
- Well. sure you do. It's outside.

711
00:54:21.550 --> 00:54:22.790
I'm guessing you're the Camaro.

712
00:54:22.801 --> 00:54:25.725
That whimsy little pickup
has Gary written all over it. Keys?

713
00:54:26.096 --> 00:54:28.269
I can't. It's Jeb's car!

714
00:54:28.474 --> 00:54:31.648
Well. won't he be surprised
when I drive it home for him.

715
00:54:38.734 --> 00:54:40.111
Who are you. mister?

716
00:54:40.611 --> 00:54:41.783
Really?

717
00:54:48.619 --> 00:54:51.247
I'm just a guy
who wants to be left alone.

718
00:54:51.789 --> 00:54:53.257
I get off work at six!

719
00:54:56.794 --> 00:54:58.512
Maybe we could...

720
00:54:58.962 --> 00:55:00.635
Sandy. listen.

721
00:55:02.424 --> 00:55:04.097
Now. you seem like a sweet girl.

722
00:55:05.093 --> 00:55:06.436
You're pretty.

723
00:55:07.471 --> 00:55:08.939
You're obviously sharp.

724
00:55:09.097 --> 00:55:10.644
doing Gary's books for him.

725
00:55:11.642 --> 00:55:13.940
You don't have to
let these guys use you.

726
00:55:16.939 --> 00:55:19.488
It's just what girls like me do.

727
00:55:23.737 --> 00:55:24.784
You got money?

728
00:55:26.114 --> 00:55:27.161
A little.

729
00:55:28.450 --> 00:55:29.997
Get out of town for a couple of days.

730
00:55:30.494 --> 00:55:31.541
Why?

731
00:55:33.831 --> 00:55:35.674
Get out of town. Sandy.

732
00:56:20.377 --> 00:56:21.424
Is Jeb home?

733
00:56:27.718 --> 00:56:30.437
I have a warrant to search the premises.

734
00:56:36.560 --> 00:56:37.903
I see.

735
00:56:40.022 --> 00:56:41.569
Well. if you don't mind...

736
00:58:49.067 --> 00:58:51.490
Get him! Get him! Get him!

737
00:59:00.245 --> 00:59:01.918
I got this!

738
00:59:01.997 --> 00:59:03.044
Okay. okay.

739
00:59:04.041 --> 00:59:05.668
All right.

740
01:00:05.477 --> 01:00:06.820
Don't move.

741
01:00:07.479 --> 01:00:08.822
I'll tell you what.

742
01:00:09.481 --> 01:00:12.109
When I move. you pull the trigger.

743
01:00:12.567 --> 01:00:14.035
Aah!

744
01:00:14.111 --> 01:00:15.408
Aah!

745
01:00:15.654 --> 01:00:17.702
- Where's Jeb?
- He's not here.

746
01:00:17.781 --> 01:00:19.124
Where can I find him?

747
01:00:19.199 --> 01:00:20.746
Jesus! My hand!

748
01:00:20.826 --> 01:00:23.067
Well. you shouldn't play with guns.
Where can I find him?

749
01:00:23.245 --> 01:00:26.169
- You're the one driving his car.
- You tell...

750
01:00:26.832 --> 01:00:29.130
The last I saw him.
we was all leaving jail.

751
01:00:29.209 --> 01:00:30.756
He said he had to see a guy.

752
01:00:30.919 --> 01:00:32.592
- What guy? Who?
- I don't know.

753
01:00:32.754 --> 01:00:34.097
I don't know. I swear.

754
01:00:34.339 --> 01:00:36.683
Next I know.
his mom woke up from a bender

755
01:00:36.758 --> 01:00:37.975
and his shit's all gone.

756
01:00:38.343 --> 01:00:40.437
Is he the sort to light out like that?

757
01:00:40.595 --> 01:00:43.098
No. no. man.
He'd never leave his moms alone.

758
01:00:43.181 --> 01:00:44.433
Shit ain't right.

759
01:00:44.516 --> 01:00:46.268
- Got a car?
- It's outside.

760
01:00:46.518 --> 01:00:47.565
Keys.

761
01:00:47.769 --> 01:00:49.362
My hand. man.
They're in my pock... Aah!

762
01:00:49.521 --> 01:00:50.864
Okay. okay.

763
01:00:57.779 --> 01:00:59.372
Now look at your friends.

764
01:00:59.948 --> 01:01:01.165
Now look at my face.

765
01:01:03.034 --> 01:01:05.207
Do you ever want to see me again?

766
01:01:05.954 --> 01:01:07.046
No way.

767
01:01:08.373 --> 01:01:10.046
Am I stealing your car?

768
01:01:10.876 --> 01:01:14.346
Use it as long as you like.

769
01:01:15.630 --> 01:01:17.007
You're very kind.

770
01:01:17.257 --> 01:01:18.383
Ah!

771
01:01:42.407 --> 01:01:43.954
<i>I think Jeb Oliver's dead.</i>

772
01:01:44.492 --> 01:01:47.496
- Who's Jeb Oliver?
- He was the guy from the bar.

773
01:01:49.080 --> 01:01:51.424
Jesus. how hard did you hit him?

774
01:01:52.250 --> 01:01:54.594
What? No. not me.

775
01:01:55.420 --> 01:01:57.047
No. he was murdered.

776
01:01:57.130 --> 01:01:59.007
And someone tried to make it
look like he left town.

777
01:01:59.090 --> 01:02:00.592
Well. maybe he just left town.

778
01:02:00.675 --> 01:02:02.435
You pack your shower curtain
when you travel?

779
01:02:02.594 --> 01:02:04.642
Is this what you base
your conclusions on?

780
01:02:04.721 --> 01:02:06.519
What is that on your head?

781
01:02:07.807 --> 01:02:08.854
Uh...

782
01:02:13.188 --> 01:02:14.565
You don't want to know.

783
01:02:16.983 --> 01:02:19.532
You said on the phone
you wanted to submit your findings.

784
01:02:22.113 --> 01:02:25.458
James Barr was a sniper.
Not the best. not the worst.

785
01:02:25.700 --> 01:02:27.452
But he trained non-stop for two years.

786
01:02:27.535 --> 01:02:28.815
What does training like that do?

787
01:02:28.954 --> 01:02:30.831
What does any training do?

788
01:02:30.914 --> 01:02:33.793
Skills become reflex. Muscle memory.
You do without thinking.

789
01:02:33.875 --> 01:02:37.470
It also makes people who aren't
necessarily smart seem smart

790
01:02:37.712 --> 01:02:39.965
by beating some
tactical awareness into them.

791
01:02:40.215 --> 01:02:42.468
Now. 99% of the evidence
your father has against Barr

792
01:02:42.550 --> 01:02:44.143
didn't exist in Baghdad.

793
01:02:44.219 --> 01:02:47.189
not because Barr was smart.
but because he was trained.

794
01:02:47.722 --> 01:02:51.397
<i>See. from that garage.
the shooter had the sun in his eyes.</i>

795
01:02:51.559 --> 01:02:54.654
<i>Targets were moving left and right.
It's difficult conditions for any sniper.</i>

796
01:02:54.729 --> 01:02:57.403
But Baghdad. you said Barr
was in a parking garage then.

797
01:02:57.482 --> 01:03:00.201
Because in Baghdad.
the sun's behind him.

798
01:03:00.402 --> 01:03:03.155
<i>Targets coming straight ahead.
single file.</i>

799
01:03:03.530 --> 01:03:06.033
Ideal conditions
for even an average shooter

800
01:03:07.075 --> 01:03:08.827
and the exact same conditions

801
01:03:08.994 --> 01:03:11.372
<i>he would've had
up on that highway bridge.</i>

802
01:03:12.247 --> 01:03:15.467
<i>Up there. he would never even
have to get out of the van.</i>

803
01:03:17.002 --> 01:03:18.470
<i>No parking meter.</i>

804
01:03:18.670 --> 01:03:19.717
<i>No camera.</i>

805
01:03:20.171 --> 01:03:24.221
<i>No trace evidence left behind.
And his escape is assured.</i>

806
01:03:24.342 --> 01:03:26.015
Now. I'm not saying
that he couldn't have killed

807
01:03:26.094 --> 01:03:28.517
those people at the river.
but he wouldn't have.

808
01:03:28.596 --> 01:03:29.643
Not that way.

809
01:03:29.723 --> 01:03:31.191
- So you're saying he's crazy.
- No.

810
01:03:31.266 --> 01:03:33.268
Well. what exactly are you saying?

811
01:03:33.351 --> 01:03:37.026
Any single piece of evidence I'd buy.
But all of it?

812
01:03:37.105 --> 01:03:39.733
Fibres. fingerprints. stray brass.
I mean...

813
01:03:39.816 --> 01:03:41.818
And who the hell pays for parking?

814
01:03:42.027 --> 01:03:44.701
Sane or crazy.
that just doesn't make sense.

815
01:03:44.779 --> 01:03:49.455
Okay. So Barr. he wanted to get caught
and he wanted you to catch him.

816
01:03:50.285 --> 01:03:52.379
That would not explain how Barr.

817
01:03:53.371 --> 01:03:57.626
an average shooter firing
in poor conditions. never missed.

818
01:03:57.792 --> 01:03:58.964
He did miss.

819
01:03:59.377 --> 01:04:00.594
He did.

820
01:04:03.715 --> 01:04:04.932
A pristine bullet.

821
01:04:05.884 --> 01:04:08.353
<i>conveniently trapped
by a liquid backstop.</i>

822
01:04:10.347 --> 01:04:12.896
The same bullet that tied
Barr's gun to the killings.

823
01:04:13.516 --> 01:04:16.861
And arguably the prosecution's single
most important piece of evidence.

824
01:04:17.354 --> 01:04:20.574
If Barr wanted to get caught.
he didn't miss.

825
01:04:21.191 --> 01:04:22.552
Either way. it doesn't make sense.

826
01:04:22.734 --> 01:04:25.078
If he wanted to get away with it.
he likely would have

827
01:04:25.195 --> 01:04:26.868
and if he wanted to get caught.

828
01:04:27.197 --> 01:04:29.791
Barr was incapable of such perfection.

829
01:04:29.908 --> 01:04:31.828
Or maybe he just got lucky.
six shots out of six.

830
01:04:32.035 --> 01:04:34.083
That's what I was willing to accept.

831
01:04:34.204 --> 01:04:36.127
then those guys took a run at me.

832
01:04:36.581 --> 01:04:38.709
Whoever sent them made a mistake.

833
01:04:38.917 --> 01:04:41.261
It was just a bar fight.

834
01:04:41.544 --> 01:04:42.716
Maybe.

835
01:04:43.755 --> 01:04:46.599
Or maybe someone got nervous.
tried to run me off.

836
01:04:47.092 --> 01:04:51.393
Or put me in a coma.
right next to their patsy.

837
01:04:54.265 --> 01:04:55.767
Patsy?

838
01:04:57.102 --> 01:04:59.730
It was such a great crime scene.

839
01:04:59.813 --> 01:05:01.781
No one stopped to think
it might be too great.

840
01:05:02.232 --> 01:05:03.404
<i>Not Emerson.</i>

841
01:05:03.566 --> 01:05:05.239
<i>Not your father.</i>

842
01:05:05.610 --> 01:05:07.954
<i>Not even Barr's own defence attorney.</i>

843
01:05:09.614 --> 01:05:11.287
<i>But Barr knew I would.</i>

844
01:05:12.951 --> 01:05:15.625
no matter how much
I wanted it to be true.

845
01:05:17.580 --> 01:05:19.332
That's why he asked for me.

846
01:05:20.250 --> 01:05:21.297
Wait.

847
01:05:22.460 --> 01:05:23.677
Are you suggesting...

848
01:05:23.753 --> 01:05:25.926
James Barr is innocent.

849
01:05:35.306 --> 01:05:37.104
You can see what this is. can't you?

850
01:05:38.143 --> 01:05:39.611
You've got a case in your hands

851
01:05:39.686 --> 01:05:41.814
that may be
the last case you'll ever have

852
01:05:42.981 --> 01:05:45.780
and you'll do anything
not to hit the bottom of it.

853
01:05:47.485 --> 01:05:48.611
Helen.

854
01:05:49.612 --> 01:05:51.455
You know.
you never should have retired.

855
01:05:51.656 --> 01:05:53.158
Just. look. Listen.

856
01:05:53.324 --> 01:05:54.746
For all I know. you were
standing at an intersection

857
01:05:54.826 --> 01:05:56.306
with a cardboard sign three days ago.

858
01:05:56.327 --> 01:05:58.625
And I hired you.
Jesus. my father was right.

859
01:05:59.164 --> 01:06:01.792
- Helen. Helen.
- It makes total sense now.

860
01:06:01.958 --> 01:06:03.710
It's the way you live.
the way you move around.

861
01:06:03.793 --> 01:06:06.467
You're just not cut out
for the real world. are you?

862
01:06:06.796 --> 01:06:08.048
Are you afraid you'll end up like Barr?

863
01:06:08.131 --> 01:06:09.371
- Helen.
- Is that what this is?

864
01:06:09.466 --> 01:06:10.513
Look out the window.

865
01:06:10.675 --> 01:06:11.972
No. I have work to do.

866
01:06:12.051 --> 01:06:13.303
- And you need to leave.
- Just humour me. Okay.

867
01:06:13.845 --> 01:06:14.892
Let go of me.

868
01:06:16.514 --> 01:06:18.482
- Would you tell me what you see?
- I see the same

869
01:06:19.851 --> 01:06:22.149
things I see every day.

870
01:06:22.353 --> 01:06:24.355
Well. imagine you've never seen it.

871
01:06:25.857 --> 01:06:28.861
Imagine you've spent your whole life
in other parts of the world

872
01:06:29.194 --> 01:06:31.697
being told every day
you're defending freedom.

873
01:06:31.988 --> 01:06:34.161
And finally
you decide you've had enough.

874
01:06:35.033 --> 01:06:38.253
Time to see
what you've given up your whole life for.

875
01:06:38.453 --> 01:06:40.956
Maybe get some of that freedom
for yourself.

876
01:06:42.707 --> 01:06:44.129
Look at the people.

877
01:06:45.710 --> 01:06:47.712
Now tell me which ones are free.

878
01:06:49.297 --> 01:06:50.970
Free from debt.

879
01:06:51.382 --> 01:06:52.634
Anxiety.

880
01:06:52.717 --> 01:06:53.969
Stress.

881
01:06:54.052 --> 01:06:55.304
Fear.

882
01:06:55.386 --> 01:06:59.061
Failure. Indignity. Betrayal.

883
01:07:01.559 --> 01:07:04.563
How many wish they were born
knowing what they know now?

884
01:07:04.646 --> 01:07:06.819
Ask yourself how many would do things

885
01:07:06.898 --> 01:07:08.571
the same way all over again?

886
01:07:09.651 --> 01:07:12.029
And how many would
live their lives like me?

887
01:07:15.406 --> 01:07:18.205
Now look at the silver Audi
across the street.

888
01:07:18.284 --> 01:07:20.252
the one that's been following me all day.

889
01:07:20.578 --> 01:07:21.921
What does that prove?

890
01:07:21.996 --> 01:07:25.421
Here's the tag number.
How long would it take you to run it?

891
01:07:25.500 --> 01:07:28.003
At this time of night?
I don't know. An hour?

892
01:07:28.086 --> 01:07:29.212
Do it.

893
01:07:29.921 --> 01:07:32.515
Do it. and then I'll leave.

894
01:07:41.766 --> 01:07:42.938
When?

895
01:07:45.937 --> 01:07:50.192
No. this is my problem now.
I'll handle it.

896
01:07:52.193 --> 01:07:53.319
Yeah?

897
01:07:55.446 --> 01:07:56.538
You're blown.

898
01:07:57.031 --> 01:07:59.284
The lawyer's running the license plates.

899
01:08:00.618 --> 01:08:02.120
Yeah. So do it?

900
01:08:03.871 --> 01:08:04.918
Done.

901
01:08:07.625 --> 01:08:09.298
Go to this address.

902
01:08:11.796 --> 01:08:14.424
All right. let’s just say
that Barr didn't do it.

903
01:08:14.549 --> 01:08:16.392
Or did it 'cause someone
put him up to it.

904
01:08:16.467 --> 01:08:17.667
Either way. what have you got?

905
01:08:17.719 --> 01:08:18.811
Conspiracy.

906
01:08:18.886 --> 01:08:20.684
Yeah. conspiracy to kill
five random people?

907
01:08:20.763 --> 01:08:22.060
There's no motive.

908
01:08:22.140 --> 01:08:24.484
- It's ridiculous. right?
- It's grassy knoll ludicrous.

909
01:08:24.642 --> 01:08:26.394
No point looking any further.

910
01:08:26.561 --> 01:08:27.983
Exactly.

911
01:08:28.521 --> 01:08:29.613
Exactly.

912
01:08:33.151 --> 01:08:34.573
What's this?

913
01:08:34.736 --> 01:08:36.830
The motive. Just hold onto it.

914
01:08:36.904 --> 01:08:38.121
What are we playing. Clue?

915
01:08:39.991 --> 01:08:41.117
Yeah?

916
01:08:42.493 --> 01:08:43.836
Give it to me.

917
01:08:48.666 --> 01:08:50.213
Thank you.

918
01:09:07.101 --> 01:09:09.775
You sure
that car was following you all day?

919
01:09:10.021 --> 01:09:11.864
As soon as you picked me up. Why?

920
01:09:18.154 --> 01:09:21.954
It's registered to a company
called Lebendauer Enterprises.

921
01:09:32.543 --> 01:09:35.888
A conspiracy to kill five random people?

922
01:09:37.215 --> 01:09:38.717
That's ridiculous.

923
01:09:41.219 --> 01:09:42.562
Four.

924
01:09:44.055 --> 01:09:45.898
Four random people.

925
01:09:47.392 --> 01:09:49.520
To hide one specific target.

926
01:10:13.710 --> 01:10:17.214
Someone needed
Oline Archer's construction business.

927
01:10:19.882 --> 01:10:22.305
<i>And Oline wouldn't let it go.</i>

928
01:10:32.562 --> 01:10:34.815
It's a convincing theory.

929
01:10:37.650 --> 01:10:39.493
But it's just a theory.

930
01:10:40.820 --> 01:10:45.326
The first round is the least accurate.
The snipers call it a cold shot.

931
01:10:45.575 --> 01:10:47.669
Meanwhile. your eyewitness
described a pause

932
01:10:47.827 --> 01:10:50.080
<i>between the first and second rounds.</i>

933
01:10:50.663 --> 01:10:53.086
<i>The one shot where the killer
took his time.</i>

934
01:10:53.332 --> 01:10:55.926
<i>And Oline Archer
was the second victim.</i>

935
01:10:56.169 --> 01:10:58.843
The one shot that mattered.

936
01:11:00.673 --> 01:11:02.300
But it's just a theory.

937
01:11:03.676 --> 01:11:05.428
This frame was custom made for Barr.

938
01:11:06.345 --> 01:11:08.222
Whoever chose him
knew about Baghdad

939
01:11:08.306 --> 01:11:09.979
and the only one who could have
told him about Baghdad

940
01:11:10.057 --> 01:11:11.604
was Barr himself.

941
01:11:11.684 --> 01:11:15.188
He has at least one friend.
A very close one.

942
01:11:15.521 --> 01:11:17.865
Now. you find that friend.
you'll find the real shooter.

943
01:11:18.107 --> 01:11:19.609
Find the real shooter? Reacher.

944
01:11:19.692 --> 01:11:22.536
my job is to present the jury
with reasonable doubt. Period.

945
01:11:22.612 --> 01:11:24.114
What about catching the guys
who really did this?

946
01:11:24.197 --> 01:11:26.291
- Catching the guys who did this?
- Bringing them to justice?

947
01:11:26.365 --> 01:11:28.526
- No. I can't take this to court.
- Exposing the truth.

948
01:11:28.534 --> 01:11:32.209
Even if I believed Barr is innocent.
it's not my job.

949
01:11:33.039 --> 01:11:36.714
I am just a lawyer. I'm not a cop.

950
01:11:39.879 --> 01:11:41.881
And frankly. neither are you.

951
01:11:45.718 --> 01:11:47.720
I can't do this any more.

952
01:11:52.600 --> 01:11:54.443
Thanks for the coffee. counsellor.

953
01:12:30.221 --> 01:12:31.393
Sandy?

954
01:12:34.934 --> 01:12:36.402
Wait. it is Sandy. isn't it?

955
01:12:38.604 --> 01:12:39.651
Do I know you?

956
01:12:41.440 --> 01:12:44.159
Charlie. Jeb's friend?

957
01:12:44.694 --> 01:12:46.412
Oh. come on. don't break my heart.

958
01:12:47.446 --> 01:12:49.039
I'm sorry. I don't remember.

959
01:12:50.116 --> 01:12:51.993
Well. we were both pretty wasted.

960
01:12:53.661 --> 01:12:54.753
Oh.

961
01:12:55.997 --> 01:12:57.840
- Yeah.

962
01:12:58.958 --> 01:13:01.802
- What. you live here?
- Just up there.

963
01:13:02.128 --> 01:13:03.471
No shit.

964
01:13:04.005 --> 01:13:07.179
I just moved in around the back!
How crazy is that?

965
01:13:07.800 --> 01:13:09.017
It's wild.

966
01:13:09.093 --> 01:13:10.140
Yeah.

967
01:13:11.470 --> 01:13:14.974
Wow! You look great.

968
01:13:15.808 --> 01:13:17.105
Thanks.

969
01:13:18.144 --> 01:13:21.364
Well. look. you know.
I don't want to keep you. so...

970
01:13:21.439 --> 01:13:23.032
Maybe we can grab a drink sometime.

971
01:13:23.149 --> 01:13:24.571
Yeah. maybe.

972
01:13:25.985 --> 01:13:27.407
Hey. how about tonight?

973
01:13:28.738 --> 01:13:30.456
I'm meeting some people.

974
01:13:31.157 --> 01:13:34.206
Okay. Well. some other time. then.

975
01:13:34.493 --> 01:13:35.836
Some other time.

976
01:13:35.912 --> 01:13:37.004
Do it here.

977
01:13:37.121 --> 01:13:38.168
What?

978
01:14:20.539 --> 01:14:21.711
Reacher!

979
01:14:37.056 --> 01:14:40.731
There's a gun range in Ohio.
targets out to 700 yards.

980
01:14:41.227 --> 01:14:43.901
The only range
that matches your requirements.

981
01:14:48.567 --> 01:14:49.989
You should sleep.

982
01:14:51.737 --> 01:14:53.159
You have a long drive tomorrow.

983
01:14:53.239 --> 01:14:55.913
and I need to go to city hall
and pull up Oline's legal history.

984
01:14:57.743 --> 01:15:00.917
I wouldn't do that. Not till I get back.

985
01:15:01.414 --> 01:15:04.213
If I'm right.
someone killed four random people

986
01:15:04.291 --> 01:15:06.464
so no one would look directly at Oline.

987
01:15:06.836 --> 01:15:10.340
And if I'm right. just saying her name
could get you killed.

988
01:15:10.423 --> 01:15:13.176
- You saying I should be scared?
- Well. are you smart?

989
01:15:13.676 --> 01:15:14.723
Obviously.

990
01:15:14.927 --> 01:15:16.179
Then don't be scared.

991
01:15:48.961 --> 01:15:51.134
What exactly am I looking for?

992
01:15:51.630 --> 01:15:54.804
Someone who could kill that girl
with one punch.

993
01:15:55.968 --> 01:15:58.312
Oh. you want the guy in 1109.

994
01:15:59.138 --> 01:16:00.640
Ernie Johnson.

995
01:16:02.224 --> 01:16:03.271
You'll see.

996
01:17:28.894 --> 01:17:30.441
Out of the car!

997
01:17:37.403 --> 01:17:40.247
That's our suspect! Move. move!

998
01:18:01.760 --> 01:18:04.183
Suspect is headed north
on State Route 65.

999
01:18:04.263 --> 01:18:05.856
I need backup and air support.

1000
01:23:38.138 --> 01:23:39.481
Hold up!

1001
01:23:39.848 --> 01:23:41.191
All clear!

1002
01:24:03.372 --> 01:24:06.046
Oh. God.
I just don't believe it. I don't believe it!

1003
01:24:06.166 --> 01:24:07.793
I issued the warrant an hour ago.

1004
01:24:07.876 --> 01:24:09.298
According to the victim's boss.

1005
01:24:09.378 --> 01:24:11.051
Reacher was seen at her
place of work this morning.

1006
01:24:11.338 --> 01:24:12.806
Where he threatened her boss.

1007
01:24:12.881 --> 01:24:15.885
The car he was driving tonight
belonged to a friend of Jeb Oliver's.

1008
01:24:16.009 --> 01:24:17.135
The man he assaulted.

1009
01:24:17.344 --> 01:24:18.971
No. those guys assaulted Reacher.

1010
01:24:19.054 --> 01:24:20.931
Reacher put three more men
in the hospital

1011
01:24:21.014 --> 01:24:22.494
this afternoon at Jeb Oliver's place.

1012
01:24:22.558 --> 01:24:24.731
After arriving in Jeb Oliver's car.

1013
01:24:24.851 --> 01:24:27.024
And Jeb hasn't been seen
since he left the hospital.

1014
01:24:27.229 --> 01:24:29.732
Helen. if you know where Reacher is.
you need to tell us.

1015
01:24:29.856 --> 01:24:31.358
I don't know where he is.
I have not seen him

1016
01:24:31.483 --> 01:24:33.906
since he left my office a few hours ago.

1017
01:24:36.029 --> 01:24:38.629
- I think she's telling the truth.
- Oh. you think. Dad? Fuck you!

1018
01:24:38.865 --> 01:24:40.833
Hey. I told you not to go near him.

1019
01:24:40.909 --> 01:24:43.332
You come into my home
and you treat me like I'm an accessory!

1020
01:24:43.412 --> 01:24:45.506
- Please! You know...
- All right. All right. Come on. Enough.

1021
01:24:45.581 --> 01:24:46.673
- Look. let me handle it.
- I'm not done.

1022
01:24:46.873 --> 01:24:48.113
You're both done. Just get out.

1023
01:24:53.547 --> 01:24:54.764
This is Helen.

1024
01:24:54.881 --> 01:24:56.303
<i>I'm guessing the police are there?</i>

1025
01:24:56.383 --> 01:24:57.430
Yep.

1026
01:24:57.551 --> 01:24:59.645
<i>By your response I'm guessing
I have about 30 seconds</i>

1027
01:24:59.720 --> 01:25:00.960
<i>before you hand them the phone.</i>

1028
01:25:01.054 --> 01:25:02.397
If that.

1029
01:25:02.598 --> 01:25:04.316
<i>If you believe someone
could frame Barr.</i>

1030
01:25:04.391 --> 01:25:06.769
<i>you have to believe
they could do the same to me.</i>

1031
01:25:06.893 --> 01:25:08.566
I suppose that's possible.

1032
01:25:09.771 --> 01:25:11.773
She was a sweet kid. Helen.

1033
01:25:12.941 --> 01:25:14.943
And they killed her because of me.

1034
01:25:16.278 --> 01:25:17.951
They want me to run.

1035
01:25:19.031 --> 01:25:20.032
But I won't.

1036
01:25:20.616 --> 01:25:23.039
<i>- I'm going to finish this.</i>
- No. that's not a good idea.

1037
01:25:23.118 --> 01:25:24.210
<i>Listen.</i>

1038
01:25:24.411 --> 01:25:27.415
Two things. One. I. uh...

1039
01:25:28.290 --> 01:25:29.917
I stole your car.

1040
01:25:30.917 --> 01:25:32.590
<i>If you want to end this.</i>

1041
01:25:32.711 --> 01:25:34.054
just hang up the phone
and report it missing.

1042
01:25:34.129 --> 01:25:35.301
And I'll understand.

1043
01:25:35.464 --> 01:25:36.807
And anything else?

1044
01:25:37.466 --> 01:25:39.685
I thought I'd be pushing it
if I mentioned this earlier.

1045
01:25:39.760 --> 01:25:41.637
Now I guess all bets are off.

1046
01:25:42.095 --> 01:25:44.939
You need to watch what you say
to Emerson and your father.

1047
01:25:45.140 --> 01:25:46.562
<i>I think one of them is in on it.</i>

1048
01:25:46.642 --> 01:25:48.986
All right. Thanks for calling. I have to go.

1049
01:25:49.102 --> 01:25:51.150
<i>Wait. I've been followed from day one.</i>

1050
01:25:53.106 --> 01:25:54.779
Only three people knew I was here.

1051
01:25:54.941 --> 01:25:57.160
<i>Emerson. your father and you.</i>

1052
01:25:58.153 --> 01:26:00.030
<i>You need to ask yourself.</i>

1053
01:26:00.113 --> 01:26:01.956
<i>who has the most to lose
if we clear Barr?</i>

1054
01:26:03.992 --> 01:26:06.336
<i>Who tried to warn you off me?</i>

1055
01:26:07.829 --> 01:26:10.332
<i>Of course. I could be wrong.
If you think I am.</i>

1056
01:26:10.457 --> 01:26:12.084
<i>just hand over the phone.</i>

1057
01:26:12.167 --> 01:26:13.669
There's no sense getting any deeper.

1058
01:26:14.961 --> 01:26:16.133
Who's that you're talking to?

1059
01:26:17.172 --> 01:26:18.594
The office.

1060
01:26:22.344 --> 01:26:23.812
Are we done?

1061
01:26:24.012 --> 01:26:25.138
Helen. listen.

1062
01:26:25.597 --> 01:26:26.718
- We need to...
- Good night.

1063
01:27:43.925 --> 01:27:45.927
You got some fine shooters here.

1064
01:27:46.595 --> 01:27:48.597
Fine as frog's hair.

1065
01:27:48.930 --> 01:27:50.273
Rarer. too.

1066
01:27:50.766 --> 01:27:54.066
'Cause most of them fellas out there
can't shoot worth a damn.

1067
01:27:54.603 --> 01:27:58.278
You ask them to put
three rounds in the black. well.

1068
01:27:58.940 --> 01:28:00.613
they'll suck it.

1069
01:28:03.069 --> 01:28:06.414
- I'm looking for the owner.
- That'd be me. Martin Cash.

1070
01:28:06.615 --> 01:28:08.117
Aaron Ward.

1071
01:28:08.408 --> 01:28:10.376
What can I do you for.
Mr Ward? Ward?

1072
01:28:10.452 --> 01:28:14.002
Yeah. I'm looking for a friend of mine.
We served in Iraq.

1073
01:28:14.080 --> 01:28:15.800
The guy just dropped
off the grid. you know?

1074
01:28:16.082 --> 01:28:17.880
- It happens. Yep.
- Yeah. Yeah.

1075
01:28:17.959 --> 01:28:19.256
Anyway. he was a shooter.

1076
01:28:19.377 --> 01:28:20.970
Last I heard. he lived
around here somewhere and I...

1077
01:28:21.129 --> 01:28:23.097
When did he get out of the Army?

1078
01:28:24.633 --> 01:28:26.306
Well. I didn't say the Army.

1079
01:28:26.426 --> 01:28:29.430
Well. you said you served with him.
You're no jarhead.

1080
01:28:29.638 --> 01:28:32.141
Man on a flying horse could see that.

1081
01:28:32.265 --> 01:28:34.438
Well. my father was in the Corps.
if that helps.

1082
01:28:34.643 --> 01:28:37.487
Well.
that makes you half human.

1083
01:28:39.105 --> 01:28:40.277
Your friend got a name?

1084
01:28:40.732 --> 01:28:42.575
Yeah. James Barr.

1085
01:28:43.819 --> 01:28:45.162
James Barr.

1086
01:28:45.821 --> 01:28:47.073
Never heard of him.

1087
01:28:48.448 --> 01:28:49.950
I think you have.

1088
01:28:51.159 --> 01:28:53.002
I think you've been dreading the moment

1089
01:28:53.119 --> 01:28:55.167
some cop comes in here
asking after him.

1090
01:28:55.497 --> 01:28:58.171
Because it's for sure
some soccer mom around here

1091
01:28:58.291 --> 01:29:02.637
is more worried about your range than
she is about the pool in her backyard

1092
01:29:02.838 --> 01:29:05.307
or the drain cleaner under her sink.

1093
01:29:06.842 --> 01:29:10.187
Wouldn't matter to her
if Barr did his killing 100 miles away.

1094
01:29:10.262 --> 01:29:12.139
only that he came hereto rehearse.

1095
01:29:12.264 --> 01:29:13.811
She'd have a case to shut you down

1096
01:29:14.683 --> 01:29:16.856
and nothing better to do.

1097
01:29:17.811 --> 01:29:18.858
What do you want?

1098
01:29:20.480 --> 01:29:22.323
I want to know who Barr's friends were.

1099
01:29:26.486 --> 01:29:27.612
Those boys out there.

1100
01:29:28.864 --> 01:29:31.663
they're mighty touchy when it comes
to their constitutional rights.

1101
01:29:32.367 --> 01:29:35.871
Suppose I tell them a cop is in here
asking after my members?

1102
01:29:36.037 --> 01:29:37.960
- I'm not a cop.
- What are you?

1103
01:29:38.039 --> 01:29:39.131
I work for Barr's attorney.

1104
01:29:39.207 --> 01:29:41.050
We have reason to believe
he's innocent.

1105
01:29:41.167 --> 01:29:42.259
The hell you say.

1106
01:29:42.335 --> 01:29:47.057
Be that as it may. I'm the only one
who's bothered to track him this far.

1107
01:29:48.216 --> 01:29:51.846
You help me out. I'll be in your debt.

1108
01:29:52.220 --> 01:29:53.312
And if I don't?

1109
01:29:55.390 --> 01:29:57.313
Maybe you can coach soccer.

1110
01:30:02.063 --> 01:30:05.067
You put three in the centre
and maybe we'll talk.

1111
01:30:07.861 --> 01:30:09.158
Can I have a few to warm up?

1112
01:31:33.238 --> 01:31:34.956
Six inches right.

1113
01:31:35.490 --> 01:31:38.994
That's your mulligan. Mr Ward.
Play ball!

1114
01:31:39.953 --> 01:31:41.296
Let's go.

1115
01:32:26.541 --> 01:32:28.839
You're a little rusty. Mr Reacher.

1116
01:32:31.212 --> 01:32:33.840
I saw a man by that name
shoot for the Wimbledon Cup.

1117
01:32:33.965 --> 01:32:35.558
what. ten years ago.

1118
01:32:36.051 --> 01:32:39.021
And I'm pretty sure you never
played second base for the Yankees

1119
01:32:39.554 --> 01:32:41.227
in 1925.

1120
01:32:42.557 --> 01:32:43.729
Now.

1121
01:32:44.726 --> 01:32:46.228
I'll answer one question.

1122
01:32:47.353 --> 01:32:48.696
Who's your best shooter?

1123
01:32:50.190 --> 01:32:51.407
James Barr.

1124
01:32:54.903 --> 01:32:57.656
I pulled all these down
as soon as I heard about the shooting.

1125
01:33:02.744 --> 01:33:04.667
That's the best shot

1126
01:33:04.746 --> 01:33:06.919
I ever seen this side of civilian life.

1127
01:33:07.916 --> 01:33:12.342
Suppose I told you Barr wasn't this
good on his best day in the Army.

1128
01:33:12.420 --> 01:33:15.515
I handed out those targets myself.
That's my scrawl on every one.

1129
01:33:15.590 --> 01:33:17.592
Do you hang them downrange. too?

1130
01:33:17.926 --> 01:33:19.599
What. are you serious?

1131
01:33:20.261 --> 01:33:23.105
I'm saying
it's possible that Barr had a friend.

1132
01:33:23.556 --> 01:33:25.196
One who switched the targets
on the range.

1133
01:33:25.225 --> 01:33:26.568
Maybe Barr let him.

1134
01:33:26.768 --> 01:33:29.942
Made him feel like King Shit
having his name up on your wall.

1135
01:33:30.063 --> 01:33:34.443
I never saw one real shooter
who would do that for his own mother.

1136
01:33:35.944 --> 01:33:38.948
Unless he was framing his mother
for multiple murder

1137
01:33:40.281 --> 01:33:42.124
and using your range to do it.

1138
01:33:45.453 --> 01:33:47.581
Barr didn't come alone. did he?

1139
01:33:49.415 --> 01:33:52.760
You know. one of these nuts is likely
to kill you. they find that camera. there.

1140
01:33:52.961 --> 01:33:54.008
Hell. the camera's there

1141
01:33:54.087 --> 01:33:56.431
'cause one of these nuts
is likely to kill me.

1142
01:33:58.424 --> 01:33:59.596
There's Barr.

1143
01:34:00.635 --> 01:34:02.888
I always liked him. Always liked him.

1144
01:34:02.971 --> 01:34:04.063
There.

1145
01:34:05.098 --> 01:34:06.270
Him.

1146
01:34:09.644 --> 01:34:11.738
That son of a bitch.

1147
01:34:17.652 --> 01:34:19.154
Helen Rodin speaking.

1148
01:34:19.279 --> 01:34:20.952
<i>Got a candidate for our shooter.</i>

1149
01:34:21.156 --> 01:34:23.500
Picture. possible prints

1150
01:34:23.992 --> 01:34:25.994
and one pissed-off eyewitness.

1151
01:34:26.327 --> 01:34:27.749
I can't talk right now.

1152
01:34:28.830 --> 01:34:30.332
Just give me three hours to get back.

1153
01:34:30.498 --> 01:34:32.500
<i>And don't talk to anyone until I get there.</i>

1154
01:34:32.625 --> 01:34:34.468
I'll look into that. thanks.

1155
01:34:35.837 --> 01:34:38.181
This is just
what I could pull this morning.

1156
01:34:38.464 --> 01:34:42.435
Tax records. city and state
permit applications. contract bids.

1157
01:34:42.510 --> 01:34:44.228
Shell corporation in Georgia.

1158
01:34:44.304 --> 01:34:46.682
That's the one next to Russia.
not Florida.

1159
01:34:47.473 --> 01:34:51.194
They work one city at a time.
acquiring a local construction concern

1160
01:34:51.477 --> 01:34:53.320
just ahead of major civic redevelopment.

1161
01:34:53.521 --> 01:34:57.196
They build bridges no one needs.
Highways no one uses.

1162
01:34:57.525 --> 01:35:02.031
They're like a cancer.
A cell that won't stop growing.

1163
01:35:03.698 --> 01:35:07.202
They moved 12 times in 15 years.
Atlanta. Albuquerque.

1164
01:35:07.327 --> 01:35:10.171
Austin. Oklahoma City. Sacramento.

1165
01:35:10.538 --> 01:35:13.382
Always amidst allegations of corruption

1166
01:35:13.499 --> 01:35:16.969
including millions of dollars
in missing public funds.

1167
01:35:17.045 --> 01:35:21.391
And yet never an investigation.
Never even an inquiry.

1168
01:35:21.883 --> 01:35:25.558
It's as if Lebendauer Enterprises
were above reproach.

1169
01:35:29.515 --> 01:35:32.143
Well. maybe that's because

1170
01:35:33.645 --> 01:35:36.023
the allegations come
from the competition.

1171
01:35:37.398 --> 01:35:39.025
Outbid. Bitter.

1172
01:35:39.567 --> 01:35:41.069
Like Oline Archer.

1173
01:35:41.569 --> 01:35:44.994
Or maybe Lebendauer
has the cooperation of key officials.

1174
01:35:45.073 --> 01:35:48.043
And maybe
when that cooperation isn't enough.

1175
01:35:48.409 --> 01:35:51.663
they kill people who won't be bought off.
Like Oline Archer.

1176
01:35:51.746 --> 01:35:53.919
Helen. how much of this
do you honestly believe?

1177
01:35:54.040 --> 01:35:56.213
It doesn't matter how much I believe.

1178
01:35:56.918 --> 01:35:58.841
It doesn't even matter
how much I can prove.

1179
01:35:58.920 --> 01:36:01.423
It only matters how much is true.

1180
01:36:01.714 --> 01:36:03.716
Do you know how delusional you sound?

1181
01:36:04.217 --> 01:36:05.890
What happened to you?

1182
01:36:06.261 --> 01:36:10.437
Are you really so set on putting
this man to death that you'd ignore...

1183
01:36:21.776 --> 01:36:24.950
I pulled all of this paper
under my own name.

1184
01:36:25.947 --> 01:36:27.790
If Jack Reacher's right.

1185
01:36:28.283 --> 01:36:31.628
my life. your daughter's life.

1186
01:36:32.287 --> 01:36:34.130
is in danger now.

1187
01:36:35.790 --> 01:36:37.792
Whatever happens to me next
is on your head.

1188
01:36:38.251 --> 01:36:40.219
whether you're involved or not.

1189
01:36:42.964 --> 01:36:47.060
You are the District Attorney
and I've given you compelling evidence

1190
01:36:47.135 --> 01:36:49.058
to investigate Lebendauer Enterprises.

1191
01:36:49.470 --> 01:36:53.316
Your next move
will tell me which side you're on.

1192
01:36:53.933 --> 01:36:54.980
Oh.

1193
01:36:56.144 --> 01:36:57.612
I see. It's a test.

1194
01:36:58.771 --> 01:37:03.652
Well. this may be hard for you
to believe. but I do love you.

1195
01:37:05.653 --> 01:37:08.156
And obviously I'm not
going to turn a blind eye.

1196
01:37:08.281 --> 01:37:10.659
no matter how absurd I find all of this.

1197
01:37:11.993 --> 01:37:15.623
So. if you really believe
that you're in danger.

1198
01:37:15.997 --> 01:37:17.499
if you believe that.

1199
01:37:18.833 --> 01:37:20.961
then the next order of business.

1200
01:37:22.003 --> 01:37:25.177
is to put you
in protective custody right now.

1201
01:37:28.343 --> 01:37:30.266
And how safe will I be
if you're part of it?

1202
01:37:30.678 --> 01:37:32.305
Jesus. Helen.

1203
01:38:22.730 --> 01:38:24.323
Oh. Hey.

1204
01:38:33.408 --> 01:38:35.035
Business meeting or personal?

1205
01:38:35.243 --> 01:38:37.245
Hard to tell them apart.

1206
01:38:37.703 --> 01:38:39.080
I'll bet.

1207
01:39:41.267 --> 01:39:42.314
Helen?

1208
01:39:42.560 --> 01:39:43.561
<i>No.</i>

1209
01:39:45.271 --> 01:39:46.614
Sorry. wrong number.

1210
01:39:46.939 --> 01:39:48.566
<i>Is this Reacher?</i>

1211
01:39:50.943 --> 01:39:52.069
Who is this?

1212
01:39:55.281 --> 01:39:57.625
Is this Reacher?

1213
01:40:02.455 --> 01:40:05.584
It's you. The guy from the car.

1214
01:40:08.085 --> 01:40:09.302
It's your boyfriend.

1215
01:40:11.130 --> 01:40:12.473
Reacher. is it you?

1216
01:40:14.091 --> 01:40:15.092
Helen. are you hurt?

1217
01:40:15.301 --> 01:40:17.341
Well. she's gonna be
if you're not here in one hour.

1218
01:40:18.095 --> 01:40:20.143
Do I have to tell you how this works?

1219
01:40:20.264 --> 01:40:22.062
You'll bounce me around
to make sure I'm not followed.

1220
01:40:22.141 --> 01:40:24.610
then walk me into
an ambush and kill me.

1221
01:40:24.810 --> 01:40:26.983
<i>Aw. you ruined my surprise.</i>

1222
01:40:27.271 --> 01:40:28.944
Well. I can do one better.

1223
01:40:29.440 --> 01:40:31.659
I went down to the gun range
at Hinge Creek.

1224
01:40:32.276 --> 01:40:35.621
<i>I got the picture. prints.
and I'm going to the Feds.</i>

1225
01:40:35.780 --> 01:40:37.453
The lawyer's all yours.

1226
01:40:41.953 --> 01:40:43.000
Get the Zec.

1227
01:40:52.463 --> 01:40:54.511
On second thought. I'd like to kill you.

1228
01:40:54.799 --> 01:40:56.221
<i>Let's say winner take all.</i>

1229
01:40:56.300 --> 01:40:57.347
Listen to me. you prick.

1230
01:40:57.468 --> 01:40:59.468
I will kill this bitch
if you're not here in one...

1231
01:41:00.846 --> 01:41:02.143
Shit!

1232
01:41:08.521 --> 01:41:10.148
<i>You think I'm a hero?</i>

1233
01:41:10.356 --> 01:41:14.202
I am not a hero.
I'm a drifter with nothing to lose.

1234
01:41:14.527 --> 01:41:17.371
You killed that girl to put me in a frame.

1235
01:41:17.488 --> 01:41:21.493
I mean to beat you to death
and drink your blood from a boot.

1236
01:41:22.368 --> 01:41:26.043
<i>Now. this is how it's going to work.
You're gonna give me the address</i>

1237
01:41:26.205 --> 01:41:28.628
and I'll be along
when I am damn good and ready.

1238
01:41:28.708 --> 01:41:30.961
If she doesn't answer the phone
when I call this number.

1239
01:41:31.043 --> 01:41:32.886
if I even think you've hurt her.

1240
01:41:33.212 --> 01:41:34.714
I disappear.

1241
01:41:34.839 --> 01:41:39.640
And if you're smart. that scares you.
because I'm in your blind spot

1242
01:41:39.719 --> 01:41:41.847
and I have nothing better to do.

1243
01:41:50.062 --> 01:41:51.109
You got a pen?

1244
01:41:53.232 --> 01:41:54.575
Don't need one.

1245
01:42:58.964 --> 01:43:03.470
If I had a dollar for every time
the Army called the Corps for help.

1246
01:43:05.805 --> 01:43:07.648
- You have something for me?
- Yeah.

1247
01:43:08.307 --> 01:43:09.775
Here.

1248
01:43:14.271 --> 01:43:15.318
You're kidding. right?

1249
01:43:15.439 --> 01:43:16.907
Just because I saw you
shoot ten years ago

1250
01:43:16.982 --> 01:43:20.452
doesn't mean I'll let you
kill some asshole with my gun.

1251
01:43:20.653 --> 01:43:22.371
I told you how serious this was.

1252
01:43:22.655 --> 01:43:24.328
And I showed up. didn't I?

1253
01:43:25.157 --> 01:43:26.329
So let's get to it.

1254
01:43:28.285 --> 01:43:29.332
<i>Now. your shooter will be</i>

1255
01:43:29.829 --> 01:43:32.924
right up there
behind those lights. Okay?

1256
01:43:32.998 --> 01:43:35.968
He can cover both roads
coming and going.

1257
01:43:36.460 --> 01:43:39.839
And kill you
just as soon as you stand up.

1258
01:43:39.964 --> 01:43:41.136
Well. can you take him out?

1259
01:43:41.674 --> 01:43:42.926
What. to dinner you mean?

1260
01:43:45.010 --> 01:43:49.356
Look. I don't know the type of people
you normally associate with. Reacher.

1261
01:43:49.682 --> 01:43:54.688
But I'm not in the habit of driving out
to the boonies at the drop of a hat

1262
01:43:55.146 --> 01:43:58.491
and just picking off
some total strangers. all right?

1263
01:43:59.358 --> 01:44:02.202
Anyway. I can't see anything.
not with them lights up.

1264
01:44:02.319 --> 01:44:03.866
So shoot them out.

1265
01:44:04.655 --> 01:44:07.408
Yeah. sure.
And then he knows right where I am.

1266
01:44:07.491 --> 01:44:09.493
I might as well set myself on fire.

1267
01:44:10.536 --> 01:44:13.415
No. sir. I'll start shooting when he does.

1268
01:44:16.041 --> 01:44:18.169
And how do you propose
we get him started?

1269
01:44:18.711 --> 01:44:22.511
Well. you could always start running.

1270
01:44:30.014 --> 01:44:31.561
What's wrong with your eye?

1271
01:44:31.682 --> 01:44:33.355
I'm saving my night vision.

1272
01:44:36.395 --> 01:44:40.571
Hey. Gunny. you mind if I ask you
kind of a personal question?

1273
01:44:40.691 --> 01:44:42.534
What. you don't think
I can shoot any more?

1274
01:44:43.235 --> 01:44:44.862
It is a perishable skill.

1275
01:44:45.738 --> 01:44:47.081
Yeah. well.

1276
01:44:47.656 --> 01:44:49.750
the sun will be up in an hour.

1277
01:44:51.243 --> 01:44:52.586
Let's get going.

1278
01:45:09.595 --> 01:45:11.768
I heard them call you the Zec.

1279
01:45:12.556 --> 01:45:13.899
That means "prisoner."

1280
01:45:15.768 --> 01:45:16.940
Yes?

1281
01:45:19.855 --> 01:45:21.277
Tell me. killing all those people.

1282
01:45:22.024 --> 01:45:23.526
I have to believe the money
you're making

1283
01:45:23.609 --> 01:45:25.031
can't possibly be enough to just...

1284
01:45:25.110 --> 01:45:26.362
Enough?

1285
01:45:26.612 --> 01:45:28.455
There is no such thing.

1286
01:45:28.781 --> 01:45:30.783
We take what can be taken.

1287
01:45:31.116 --> 01:45:32.663
This is what we do.

1288
01:45:35.120 --> 01:45:36.463
And you?

1289
01:45:38.123 --> 01:45:40.717
This one I think I understand. but you?

1290
01:45:41.377 --> 01:45:42.469
Why'd you do it?

1291
01:45:42.795 --> 01:45:45.139
You make it sound like I had a choice.

1292
01:45:45.297 --> 01:45:46.469
Oh. didn't you?

1293
01:45:49.969 --> 01:45:51.312
You'll see.

1294
01:45:55.140 --> 01:45:58.485
You should know I've taken steps.
that if anything happens...

1295
01:45:58.561 --> 01:46:02.282
if anything happens to you.
it will happen in front of your father

1296
01:46:02.398 --> 01:46:04.446
while he begs for your life.

1297
01:46:06.652 --> 01:46:08.996
You should never have involved him.

1298
01:46:09.321 --> 01:46:13.042
Now you will have to convince him
to forget. for your sake

1299
01:46:13.117 --> 01:46:15.370
and for his.

1300
01:46:16.245 --> 01:46:19.920
You say nothing.
but I see defiance in your eyes.

1301
01:46:20.666 --> 01:46:23.510
That is a look I have seen
many. many times.

1302
01:46:23.836 --> 01:46:26.180
When the soldier comes.

1303
01:46:26.255 --> 01:46:28.678
when you watch how he dies.
it will change you.

1304
01:46:29.174 --> 01:46:31.393
You will want to forget me then.

1305
01:46:42.187 --> 01:46:43.439
Reacher?

1306
01:46:43.522 --> 01:46:44.865
<i>Are you okay?</i>

1307
01:46:45.107 --> 01:46:46.324
They're ready for you.

1308
01:46:47.276 --> 01:46:48.903
They'd like to think so.

1309
01:46:49.862 --> 01:46:52.365
Don't do this.
Please don't do this. Not for me.

1310
01:46:52.448 --> 01:46:54.075
<i>Listen. Helen. they're not gonna</i>

1311
01:46:54.199 --> 01:46:58.170
hurt you until they have me.
And that's never going to happen.

1312
01:46:58.370 --> 01:46:59.542
<i>You hear me?</i>

1313
01:47:00.623 --> 01:47:01.715
You just hang in there.

1314
01:47:03.542 --> 01:47:05.385
'Cause I'm coming to get you.

1315
01:47:07.129 --> 01:47:08.472
Now say you believe me.

1316
01:47:09.965 --> 01:47:11.342
I believe you.

1317
01:47:43.165 --> 01:47:45.042
This was a bad idea.

1318
01:48:03.936 --> 01:48:05.563
Any time now. Gunny.

1319
01:48:20.619 --> 01:48:22.212
Shit.

1320
01:48:33.882 --> 01:48:35.429
Where the hell are you. Gunny?

1321
01:52:53.725 --> 01:52:55.398
Suck it!

1322
01:53:06.571 --> 01:53:08.073
You should go.

1323
01:53:51.283 --> 01:53:52.626
Toss it.

1324
01:56:51.046 --> 01:56:53.140
I know you're in there. Emerson.

1325
01:56:56.968 --> 01:56:59.642
It was staring me right in the face.

1326
01:57:01.306 --> 01:57:04.810
The one piece that just didn't fit.

1327
01:57:05.644 --> 01:57:07.112
The quarter.

1328
01:57:09.481 --> 01:57:12.451
Nobody would have thought
to dump that meter.

1329
01:57:14.152 --> 01:57:15.654
Not even me.

1330
01:57:59.155 --> 01:58:01.157
You were wrong about my father.

1331
01:58:03.159 --> 01:58:05.287
I wouldn't make a big thing of it.

1332
01:58:22.637 --> 01:58:23.854
Who is he?

1333
01:58:23.972 --> 01:58:25.519
That's John Doe Number Two.

1334
01:58:25.682 --> 01:58:28.856
The man on the grassy knoll.
The thing under the bed.

1335
01:58:30.020 --> 01:58:31.693
They call him the Zec.

1336
01:58:31.980 --> 01:58:34.199
Zec? Prisoner.

1337
01:58:35.317 --> 01:58:36.694
What's your real name?

1338
01:58:39.863 --> 01:58:41.615
I was born in October.

1339
01:58:41.698 --> 01:58:44.042
When I get to my birthday.
I'm gonna pull the trigger.

1340
01:58:44.367 --> 01:58:46.290
One. Two.

1341
01:58:46.369 --> 01:58:49.999
Chelovek. Zec Chelovek.

1342
01:58:51.708 --> 01:58:53.210
Chelovek?

1343
01:58:53.877 --> 01:58:55.379
Chelovek? Human.

1344
01:58:57.380 --> 01:58:58.927
Prisoner Human Being.

1345
01:59:00.050 --> 01:59:03.395
- That's your real name?
- That is all I remember.

1346
01:59:06.556 --> 01:59:08.024
Call the police.

1347
01:59:11.561 --> 01:59:13.359
Were you really going to shoot him?

1348
01:59:15.065 --> 01:59:16.908
I knew I wouldn't have to.

1349
01:59:18.026 --> 01:59:21.906
One look at this guy and you know
he'll do anything to survive.

1350
01:59:22.238 --> 01:59:24.411
One look at me
and you know I'm not bluffing.

1351
01:59:24.699 --> 01:59:27.202
Yes. I have an emergency at...

1352
01:59:28.078 --> 01:59:29.375
Yes. I'll hold.

1353
01:59:33.083 --> 01:59:34.426
We're in no hurry.

1354
01:59:37.045 --> 01:59:39.264
With a name like yours.
you're gonna feel right at home.

1355
01:59:39.589 --> 01:59:42.263
Prison? In America?

1356
01:59:42.759 --> 01:59:46.935
A retirement home.
If I go to prison at all.

1357
01:59:47.055 --> 01:59:48.227
You think you're gonna walk?

1358
01:59:48.431 --> 01:59:51.105
You are a homeless drifter
wanted for murder.

1359
01:59:51.434 --> 01:59:55.780
Meanwhile. I am an old man
in the wrong place at the wrong time.

1360
01:59:56.106 --> 02:00:00.202
Thanks to you.
who is left to say otherwise? Who?

1361
02:00:00.276 --> 02:00:04.122
Yes. hello? Yes. there's...
I have an emergency.

1362
02:00:04.239 --> 02:00:06.287
We'll see which one of us
goes to prison.

1363
02:00:06.449 --> 02:00:08.952
There are maybe
three. four people dead.

1364
02:00:10.495 --> 02:00:11.963
- Okay.
- My bet?

1365
02:00:13.623 --> 02:00:15.000
Neither one.

1366
02:00:18.128 --> 02:00:19.675
What did you do?

1367
02:00:24.134 --> 02:00:25.681
What's it look like?

1368
02:00:27.429 --> 02:00:28.476
What about the truth?

1369
02:00:28.972 --> 02:00:31.395
What about getting the guys
who really did this?

1370
02:00:31.474 --> 02:00:33.476
What about bringing him to justice?

1371
02:00:34.644 --> 02:00:36.271
I just did.

1372
02:00:43.820 --> 02:00:46.949
What about clearing Barr?
What about clearing you?

1373
02:00:47.157 --> 02:00:48.797
I have faith you'll sort it out.

1374
02:00:48.825 --> 02:00:50.668
And I hear you have an in
with the local D.A.

1375
02:00:50.785 --> 02:00:53.004
But what happens to you
in the meantime?

1376
02:00:53.163 --> 02:00:55.006
I keep moving. Same as always.

1377
02:00:55.123 --> 02:00:57.296
Wait. is that my car?

1378
02:01:04.257 --> 02:01:05.304
This the lady?

1379
02:01:06.176 --> 02:01:08.349
Helen Rodin. Martin Cash.

1380
02:01:08.678 --> 02:01:09.804
A pleasure.

1381
02:01:11.181 --> 02:01:13.354
You look like hell there. Army.

1382
02:01:13.475 --> 02:01:17.150
You asked if I was afraid
I'd end up like Barr. I'm not.

1383
02:01:17.353 --> 02:01:19.196
I'm afraid I'll end up like this guy.

1384
02:01:19.314 --> 02:01:22.113
There's a lot of dead bodies out here.
So let's get to it.

1385
02:01:22.192 --> 02:01:25.036
- We should probably go.
- Wait. That's it?

1386
02:01:25.528 --> 02:01:26.700
It's just over?

1387
02:01:27.822 --> 02:01:29.540
You'll be all right. counsellor.

1388
02:01:29.699 --> 02:01:32.373
No. What if I need you?
How will I find you?

1389
02:01:32.660 --> 02:01:33.877
You don't need me.

1390
02:01:35.497 --> 02:01:36.794
Not any more.

1391
02:01:39.375 --> 02:01:40.718
Get her number. Let's go!

1392
02:01:57.227 --> 02:01:59.229
I'm Helen Rodin. your attorney.

1393
02:02:00.230 --> 02:02:03.985
This conversation is protected
by attorney-client privilege.

1394
02:02:04.067 --> 02:02:05.068
You understand what that means?

1395
02:02:05.193 --> 02:02:06.240
Yeah.

1396
02:02:06.319 --> 02:02:08.572
Now. the police didn't
talk to you. did they?

1397
02:02:08.738 --> 02:02:10.581
They're not allowed
to do that without me here.

1398
02:02:14.577 --> 02:02:16.250
How bad was it?

1399
02:02:18.248 --> 02:02:19.591
How many did I...

1400
02:02:20.750 --> 02:02:22.752
You don't remember
anything about the incident?

1401
02:02:26.381 --> 02:02:27.428
No.

1402
02:02:28.925 --> 02:02:32.099
But I could hear the nurses
talking to those cops out there.

1403
02:02:36.266 --> 02:02:38.439
I don't even
remember wanting to do it!

1404
02:02:43.940 --> 02:02:45.283
Look. I'm not gonna fight this.

1405
02:02:46.776 --> 02:02:49.120
If they say I done it. then I did.

1406
02:02:49.779 --> 02:02:51.452
I done things before.

1407
02:02:54.117 --> 02:02:55.460
I did something bad.

1408
02:02:58.121 --> 02:02:59.293
Real bad.

1409
02:03:03.126 --> 02:03:04.799
A long time ago.

1410
02:03:08.298 --> 02:03:09.971
And I got away with it.

1411
02:03:17.640 --> 02:03:18.812
James.

1412
02:03:19.142 --> 02:03:20.985
how well do you know this place?

1413
02:03:32.280 --> 02:03:33.657
Pretty well.

1414
02:03:34.324 --> 02:03:36.044
And how do you think
you would have done it?

1415
02:03:39.495 --> 02:03:40.838
I guess

1416
02:03:46.836 --> 02:03:48.838
I would have parked up on the highway.

1417
02:03:49.297 --> 02:03:51.846
The sun would be at my back
that time of day.

1418
02:03:53.509 --> 02:03:54.635
I got a van.

1419
02:03:55.970 --> 02:03:57.643
Set up in back.

1420
02:03:58.348 --> 02:04:00.692
Wouldn't have to worry about my brass.

1421
02:04:02.518 --> 02:04:04.520
Get away real clean. too.

1422
02:04:08.024 --> 02:04:10.026
That sound about right?

1423
02:04:11.527 --> 02:04:13.700
Sounds as if you know your stuff.

1424
02:04:18.660 --> 02:04:20.037
I forget your name.

1425
02:04:20.703 --> 02:04:22.046
It's Helen.

1426
02:04:23.706 --> 02:04:25.049
Helen Rodin.

1427
02:04:30.672 --> 02:04:32.845
You're going to be okay. James.

1428
02:04:34.008 --> 02:04:35.726
I am gonna take care of you.

1429
02:04:35.885 --> 02:04:37.387
You can't protect me.

1430
02:04:40.682 --> 02:04:42.025
No one can.

1431
02:04:42.225 --> 02:04:43.568
From what?

1432
02:04:45.019 --> 02:04:46.066
From who?

1433
02:04:47.563 --> 02:04:49.236
There's this guy.

1434
02:04:52.902 --> 02:04:54.404
He's a kind of cop.

1435
02:04:56.364 --> 02:04:58.037
At least he used to be.

1436
02:04:59.242 --> 02:05:01.244
<i>He doesn't care about the</i> law.

1437
02:05:02.912 --> 02:05:04.914
<i>He doesn't care about proof.</i>

1438
02:05:06.040 --> 02:05:07.758
<i>He only cares about what's right.</i>

1439
02:05:08.084 --> 02:05:09.927
Look at me
when I'm talking to you!

1440
02:05:10.253 --> 02:05:11.755
<i>He knows what I did.</i>

1441
02:05:13.715 --> 02:05:14.762
<i>He knows where I am.</i>

1442
02:05:16.384 --> 02:05:19.263
<i>And this guy. he made me a promise.</i>

1443
02:05:19.554 --> 02:05:20.601
- I said. shut your mouth!

1444
02:05:21.764 --> 02:05:23.937
<i>If I ever got in trouble again.</i>

1445
02:05:25.601 --> 02:05:26.944
<i>he'd be there.</i>

1445
02:05:27.305 --> 02:06:27.207
